LAURA: It is that! Okay. I'm ready.

00:03:36.807 --> 00:03:38.286
MATT: All right, go for it.

00:03:38.286 --> 00:03:46.611
LAURA: Okay, it's my turn? Da da-da da! We have
new merch in the store now! We've been waiting on

00:03:46.611 --> 00:03:54.320
these ones for so long, and they're finally here!
It's so beautiful. This is the artwork that's on

00:03:54.320 --> 00:03:59.773
my save screen on my phone. It's been that way for
a long-- me and Ashley both. We're in love with

00:03:59.773 --> 00:04:06.381
this art. It's got pages so you can take all your
personal D&amp;D notes in here. That's why we did it.

00:04:06.381 --> 00:04:12.730
And it goes with our pencil set, so you can have,
you know. You can have one, Jen, if you want!

00:04:12.730 --> 00:04:14.694
TALIESIN: You can make your own art book.

00:04:14.694 --> 00:04:19.289
LAURA: So yeah, go check it out! It's in the store
now!

00:04:19.289 --> 00:04:28.007
MATT: Awesome. Thank you, Laura. Also, cool note.
The third issue of Critical Role - Vox Machina:

00:04:28.007 --> 00:04:35.331
Origins comic is available. It's getting more and
more intense as each issue goes along. Check it

00:04:35.331 --> 00:04:40.597
out if you haven't had a chance. It's on
Comixology, digital.darkhorse.com, and wherever

00:04:40.597 --> 00:04:46.268
else you can find digital comics online. It's
pretty radical. Me and Liam, who have read the

00:04:46.268 --> 00:04:51.033
