MATT: "A smear monger."

00:18:29.301 --> 00:18:31.111
LAURA: That sounds great.

00:18:31.111 --> 00:18:33.064
MATT: "A smear monger, a chandler, crafter of
light."

00:18:33.064 --> 00:18:34.436
LAURA: Of course!

00:18:34.436 --> 00:18:36.057
MATT: "A candlemaker!"

00:18:36.057 --> 00:18:37.619
TRAVIS, LAURA, TALIESIN: Oh!

00:18:37.619 --> 00:18:40.451
LAURA: What kind of candles?

00:18:40.451 --> 00:18:44.951
MATT: "Oh, all kinds of candles: scented,
colorful, sizes, long wicks, short wicks."

00:18:44.951 --> 00:18:47.438
TRAVIS: Explosive?

00:18:47.438 --> 00:18:49.736
MATT: "No, but I haven't dabbled, either."

00:18:49.736 --> 00:18:50.999
JENNIFER: Any black ones?

00:18:50.999 --> 00:18:57.530
MATT: "Ah, that'll bring us to the crux of our
conversation. There &lt;i&gt;were&lt;/i&gt;. I've been hoarding all

00:18:57.530 --> 00:19:02.615
"of the oils and fats from the kitchen since I was
a boy, slowly learning to build a stock and keep

00:19:02.615 --> 00:19:07.859
"it beneath my bed, and eventually moving it to a
shed offsite. Reading what books I can in secret.

00:19:07.859 --> 00:19:14.329
"If my father knew my interests in candle making...
anyway." And you can see his eyes begin to well up

00:19:14.329 --> 00:19:22.502
a bit and his hands are shaking. "I went to go to
my storage shed after buying a small homestead in

00:19:22.502 --> 00:19:30.282
"Goldshire and hoping to open a shop at some point
in the future. It's all gone. All of it! Just

00:19:30.282 --> 00:19:36.775
"gone! Every. Single. Candle I've made! Gone!"

00:19:36.775 --> 00:19:40.753
LAURA: Even your fat stores?

00:19:40.753 --> 00:19:47.198
MATT: "Well the fat stores are normally stored in
there, but they've gone bad since. I asked for it

00:19:47.198 --> 00:19:50.897
"to be investigated, but the guard laughed at me.
They have no appreciation for fine candlework."

00:19:50.897 --> 00:19:56.553
You notice, across the room, one of the other
women who are in there who's the local voyeur

00:19:56.553 --> 00:20:01.931
chuckles under her breath and she eats her cold
toast and stays at the table. Wental shoots her an

00:20:01.931 --> 00:20:09.200
icy dagger glance and back to you. "I ask, if you
would help retrieve my life's work, I would

00:20:09.200 --> 00:20:18.190
"greatly make it worth your while. I have my
savings, which isn't much, about 520 gold pieces.

00:20:18.190 --> 00:20:23.397
"And I could probably muster some armor that
matches."

00:20:23.397 --> 00:20:24.976
LAURA: That'd be great!

00:20:24.976 --> 00:20:26.498
MATT: "What do you say?"

00:20:26.498 --> 00:20:27.764
LAURA: Do you have robes?

00:20:27.764 --> 00:20:29.175
MATT: "That could be arranged."

00:20:29.175 --> 00:20:30.588
TALIESIN: Doesn't have to match.

00:20:30.588 --> 00:20:35.845
TRAVIS: Yeah, but we should present a united
front, though. I mean, people should be able to

00:20:35.845 --> 00:20:37.440
see that we are a group.

00:20:37.440 --> 00:20:39.206
JENNIFER: As long as it's black.

00:20:39.206 --> 00:20:40.763
LIAM: As long as it's white.

00:20:40.763 --> 00:20:43.459
TALIESIN: As long as it's lime green.

00:20:43.459 --> 00:20:45.206
LAURA: I'm partial to purple.

00:20:45.206 --> 00:20:51.201
MATT: "I'll see what I can do about dye colors.
I'll have to send away, possibly to Westfall. They

00:20:51.201 --> 00:20:57.473
"have some good dyers there. But if you agree to
this, then the sooner we can get off the better!"

00:20:57.473 --> 00:21:03.075
And he twirls his mustache with both of his
fingers, a nervous tick or an exclamation of

00:21:03.075 --> 00:21:05.328
physicality. "Shall we?"

00:21:05.328 --> 00:21:07.561
JENNIFER: I'll agree as long as you never do that
again.

00:21:07.561 --> 00:21:09.672
MATT: "Very well."

00:21:09.672 --> 00:21:12.858
TALIESIN: There was a fisherman who did like 25 of
those little red plants, but this sounds better.

00:21:12.858 --> 00:21:19.004
LAURA: This sounds fun! Wental, you can count on
us! I jump on top of the table and raise my fist

00:21:19.004 --> 00:21:20.819
into the air.

00:21:20.819 --> 00:21:22.459
JENNIFER: I shrink into my chair.

00:21:22.459 --> 00:21:25.096
MATT: He awkwardly reaches out and side fistbumps,
not sure what to do.

00:21:25.096 --> 00:21:26.839
LAURA: Candles!

00:21:26.839 --> 00:21:28.698
MATT: "I like her!"

00:21:28.698 --> 00:21:33.376
TRAVIS: I'm sure this morning's fare will be also
a part of our arrangement?

00:21:33.376 --> 00:21:35.384
MATT: "Sure."

00:21:35.384 --> 00:21:39.675
LIAM: And I was going to ask for a couple bottles
of your best vintage to be added to the agreed

00:21:39.675 --> 00:21:41.133
upon price.

00:21:41.133 --> 00:21:43.620
TRAVIS and JENNIFER: Yes.

00:21:43.620 --> 00:21:48.517
MATT: "Very well. I'll be happy to place it upon
your tab that will be wiped clean upon the

00:21:48.517 --> 00:21:50.356
"retrieval of my candles."

00:21:50.356 --> 00:21:52.912
JENNIFER: A steed or two. I saw something out back
that looked rather suitable.

00:21:52.912 --> 00:22:01.803
MATT: "I'll see what I can do. I only have so much
I can do in the town, but let me try. Anyway." And

00:22:01.803 --> 00:22:07.274
he rushes off. He comes back and he brings you two
bottles of wine, not the greatest. You don't get a

00:22:07.274 --> 00:22:12.305
lot of decent import over here on Lakeshore,
unfortunately. It's a little out of the way.

00:22:12.305 --> 00:22:13.973
LIAM: Will it mess me up?

00:22:13.973 --> 00:22:16.822
MATT: "If you were to chug it now, most likely!"

00:22:16.822 --> 00:22:18.638
LIAM: That's a deal.

00:22:18.638 --> 00:22:22.567
MATT: "All righty. Follow me. I'll take you to the
shed. See if you can learn anything."

00:22:22.567 --> 00:22:24.214
LAURA: Great.

00:22:24.214 --> 00:22:33.856
MATT: So Wental guides you outside the Lakeshore
Inn, around the back and up past some bushes.

00:22:33.856 --> 00:22:37.809
There's a number of trees that crest right against
the base of the Red Ridge Mountains, just above

00:22:37.809 --> 00:22:42.637
the location of the inn. As he comes around, you
can see there's the one stable off to the side. He

00:22:42.637 --> 00:22:49.741
goes, "I'll talk to them and see what I can do.
But to be honest, the stable master and me don't

00:22:49.741 --> 00:22:51.510
"really get along."

00:22:51.510 --> 00:22:54.270
JENNIFER: Just show me where he is. I'm sure we
can work something out.

00:22:54.270 --> 00:23:01.436
MATT: "Very well. Should I take you to the shed
first, or do you need your steed now?"

00:23:01.436 --> 00:23:03.599
LAURA: Maybe to the shed since it's close.

00:23:03.599 --> 00:23:07.641
JENNIFER: We can go to the shed. I don't want to
make the small one run.

00:23:07.641 --> 00:23:11.475
LAURA: Thank you.

00:23:11.475 --> 00:23:14.500
MATT: "I don't mind. All right." And you see he
seems to have confidence around the gnome. And

00:23:14.500 --> 00:23:18.279
then he gets really sheepish in the gaze of the
night elf who stares down and probably stands a

00:23:18.279 --> 00:23:26.289
good six inches taller than him. So he leads you
up past this section to the base of the mountains

00:23:26.289 --> 00:23:31.605
and you can see there's a really nice-looking shed
that's settled between the edge of the mountains

00:23:31.605 --> 00:23:36.416
and a tree over there. It's closed, it's locked
up, there's chains. But as you walk up, you can

00:23:36.416 --> 00:23:40.147
see that the actual lock has been broken and the
chains dangle off to the sides of the two doors

00:23:40.147 --> 00:23:42.333
that open up into it.

00:23:42.333 --> 00:23:45.385
TALIESIN: There's your trouble. You left it
unlocked.

00:23:45.385 --> 00:23:48.498
TRAVIS: I think someone broke the lock.

00:23:48.498 --> 00:23:54.626
TALIESIN: You're making assumptions, I feel.
That's a lot to just assume, just taking your

00:23:54.626 --> 00:23:56.096
first look.

00:23:56.096 --> 00:23:59.870
MATT: (squeak) He opens the front doors to the
shed and upon looking inside, you can see there

00:23:59.870 --> 00:24:06.697
are shelves arranged. There are small crates that
have been pried open. Across the entirety of the

00:24:06.697 --> 00:24:12.729
floor you see scraps of wax scattered here and
there, large spaces where apparently clusters of

00:24:12.729 --> 00:24:18.499
it were set and have since been pulled. And it is
entirely empty and scraped of any possible

00:24:18.499 --> 00:24:24.746
remainder of wax. And there's a sudden smell that
comes out, too. It could be a combination of

00:24:24.746 --> 00:24:32.949
either rotting animal bits and/or some element of
fecal matter. It's hard to really pick out. But

00:24:32.949 --> 00:24:34.522
it's not a pleasant interior.

00:24:34.522 --> 00:24:41.016
LIAM: Are there any markings, footprints,
different toe patterns, any kind of clues?

00:24:41.016 --> 00:24:45.989
MATT: "I looked everywhere and saw nothing. I'm
also a bartender and that's why I asked you guys.

00:24:45.989 --> 00:24:48.189
"So if you want to have a look, please!"

00:24:48.189 --> 00:24:51.517
LIAM: Yeah. I was actually asking the DM.

00:24:51.517 --> 00:24:54.869
MATT: Oh, okay.

00:24:54.869 --> 00:24:59.915
LIAM: Do I see, with my Draenei eyes, as I stroke
my chin tentacles--

00:24:59.915 --> 00:25:05.164
LAURA: You have tentacles?! You have tentacles on
your chin?

00:25:05.164 --> 00:25:08.235
LIAM: On my chin. I don't like to draw attention
to them.

00:25:08.235 --> 00:25:12.199
TRAVIS: You don't need to. They're just there.

00:25:12.199 --> 00:25:17.868
MATT: So are you getting to the ground?

00:25:17.868 --> 00:25:19.235
LIAM: That's right.

00:25:19.235 --> 00:25:20.843
MATT: Make an investigation check.

00:25:20.843 --> 00:25:28.912
LIAM: Yes. I'm making an investigation check. I'm
rolling a d20. That's not very good. That is, hold

00:25:28.912 --> 00:25:32.009
on! I've just solved the entire game. That's a
two.

00:25:32.009 --> 00:25:36.444
MATT: You get close to the ground and there's a
lot of small bits of wax. And you start pulling

00:25:36.444 --> 00:25:40.623
them together and piecing them, and you figure if
you spend the next couple hours, you can maybe put

00:25:40.623 --> 00:25:42.674
together a very small candle.

00:25:42.674 --> 00:25:44.470
LIAM: There were candles here.

00:25:44.470 --> 00:25:46.246
MATT: You are correct.

00:25:46.246 --> 00:25:50.533
TRAVIS: Quazi, you are astute, as always. Bundle,
would you mind checking the lock to see if

00:25:50.533 --> 00:25:51.950
there's--?

00:25:51.950 --> 00:25:54.399
TALIESIN: I take a look at the lock.

00:25:54.399 --> 00:25:55.944
MATT: Make an investigation check.

00:25:55.944 --> 00:25:58.602
TALIESIN: Oh, boy. Oh, wow.

00:25:58.602 --> 00:26:01.996
TRAVIS: Oh, no. It's cold in here.

00:26:01.996 --> 00:26:05.755
LAURA: Warm it up, guys!

00:26:05.755 --> 00:26:07.119
TALIESIN: Seven?

00:26:07.119 --> 00:26:12.435
MATT: Seven? The lock appears to have been broken
through blunt force, but you have no other

00:26:12.435 --> 00:26:14.518
information you can draw from it.

00:26:14.518 --> 00:26:18.961
TALIESIN: Lock appears to have been broken by
blunt force. I don't know.

00:26:18.961 --> 00:26:20.870
JENNIFER: Let me have a look.

00:26:20.870 --> 00:26:23.012
MATT: All right, if you want to go ahead and make
an investigation check as well.

00:26:23.012 --> 00:26:33.073
LIAM: That's a good idea. Okay, that's better than
us. So you go from there to there, and add that.

00:26:33.073 --> 00:26:35.479
JENNIFER: So it's 13.

00:26:35.479 --> 00:26:41.647
MATT: 13? So as you start glancing around, first
things first. When you get closer to the ground

00:26:41.647 --> 00:26:48.390
and elements of the doorway, you can smell in the
air, it's almost like a wet fur scent in the air.

00:26:48.390 --> 00:26:53.371
And as you glance towards the edge of the shed's
opening in the mud and dirt that surrounds the

00:26:53.371 --> 00:26:59.911
exterior, you can see faint foot tracks smattering
in different directions. Many of them. There's

00:26:59.911 --> 00:27:06.745
multiple sets. Soled shoes, or boots of some kind.
But it looks almost like there's also a toe or two

00:27:06.745 --> 00:27:15.470
protruding from the front. Smaller than a man's
feet. They lead away from the shed and then

00:27:15.470 --> 00:27:19.349
further up the mountain range to the westward
direction.

00:27:19.349 --> 00:27:28.193
JENNIFER: I've seen these before. It's been a long
time. It was very far from here. I hesitate to

00:27:28.193 --> 00:27:34.206
name it. I'll leave that to the Dungeon Master.
It's my first game!

00:27:34.206 --> 00:27:41.979
LIAM: You can also tell there were candles here,
yes?

00:27:41.979 --> 00:27:45.141
JENNIFER: Yes. I can smell there were candles
here.

00:27:45.141 --> 00:27:51.537
MATT: So, go ahead and roll a d20 and add your
intelligence modifier to this one. So, look at

00:27:51.537 --> 00:27:54.623
your intelligence. Liam, want to help her with the
intelligence modifier?

00:27:54.623 --> 00:27:57.089
LIAM: Intelligence modifier is up here, yeah? Five
plus--

00:27:57.089 --> 00:27:58.305
JENNIFER: So, 13.

00:27:58.305 --> 00:27:59.960
MATT: That's a saving throw.

00:27:59.960 --> 00:28:04.448
LIAM: Oh, so intelligence check, you say?
Intelligence check? Well, then it's just that

00:28:04.448 --> 00:28:08.569
plus-- where the hell is it? There it is.

00:28:08.569 --> 00:28:09.997
JENNIFER: Ten!

00:28:09.997 --> 00:28:16.193
MATT: Ten? Okay. You recall seeing tracks like
this before but the name is on the tip of your

00:28:16.193 --> 00:28:18.026
tongue. You're not entirely certain what it could
be.

00:28:18.026 --> 00:28:20.665
JENNIFER: The name's on the tip of my tongue and I
can't quite grab it. Can someone else grab it for

00:28:20.665 --> 00:28:21.441
me?

00:28:21.441 --> 00:28:23.765
TRAVIS: Yes. Let me see if I recognize these
tracks.

00:28:23.765 --> 00:28:30.479
LAURA: Does anyone know that you make candles?
Other than your father?

00:28:30.479 --> 00:28:34.421
MATT: "Well, he doesn't know yet. I was going to
open the store first and have him come take a look

00:28:34.421 --> 00:28:35.647
"at it."

00:28:35.647 --> 00:28:37.736
LAURA: Oh, okay. So you don't have any candle
enemies?

00:28:37.736 --> 00:28:42.195
MATT: "I don't believe so. Not in this town. There
isn't a candlemaker, not anymore."

00:28:42.195 --> 00:28:46.071
LAURA: And are your candles scented?

00:28:46.071 --> 00:28:47.602
MATT: "Some of them were."

00:28:47.602 --> 00:28:50.279
LAURA: Do most of them smell like animal fat?

00:28:50.279 --> 00:28:57.145
MATT: "Yes, they do, by their very nature. But I
try best to add lavender to the batch and

00:28:57.145 --> 00:28:58.910
"occasionally--"

00:28:58.910 --> 00:29:00.320
JENNIFER: Lavender, you say?

00:29:00.320 --> 00:29:01.457
MATT: "Yes, lavender."

00:29:01.457 --> 00:29:03.352
LIAM: What about paht-pourri?

00:29:03.352 --> 00:29:07.477
TRAVIS: We've discussed this. It's &lt;i&gt;potpourri&lt;/i&gt;.

00:29:07.477 --> 00:29:09.115
LIAM: You're dropping off the T.

00:29:09.115 --> 00:29:11.847
TRAVIS: Well, it's just potpourri.

00:29:11.847 --> 00:29:13.310
LIAM: You're fucking with me.

00:29:13.310 --> 00:29:15.008
TRAVIS: No, for the fourth time.

00:29:15.008 --> 00:29:17.514
LAURA: Were you going to track them?

00:29:17.514 --> 00:29:19.624
TRAVIS: I'd like to try.

00:29:19.624 --> 00:29:21.795
MATT: Make a survival check.

00:29:21.795 --> 00:29:23.520
TRAVIS: Natural 20.

00:29:23.520 --> 00:29:25.627
LAURA: Is that with your Grog dice?

00:29:25.627 --> 00:29:27.351
TRAVIS: With my die!

00:29:27.351 --> 00:29:36.697
MATT: You watch as the armored human paladin gets
low. His eyes suddenly spark! As he looks to the

00:29:36.697 --> 00:29:40.798
left, looks to the right, looks down to the
ground, and, almost like a hound dog, begins

00:29:40.798 --> 00:29:46.876
trailing this track curving around the shed into
the west as you guys slowly follow suit.

00:29:46.876 --> 00:29:51.117
TALIESIN: This is why we pay him big gold bucks
right there.

00:29:51.117 --> 00:29:55.009
TRAVIS: And because I'm handsome.

00:29:55.009 --> 00:29:59.278
MATT: As you guys follow, Wental stays a few steps
behind. He seems excited, but also not sure what

00:29:59.278 --> 00:30:03.056
you guys are going to discover and you can see the
tension rising in him. His shoulders are slowly

00:30:03.056 --> 00:30:05.355
creeping up across the sides of his head.

00:30:05.355 --> 00:30:10.050
LAURA: Yes, we're clearly much more experienced
fighters than you are.

00:30:10.050 --> 00:30:19.168
MATT: "I completely agree. I hope." At this point
you catch up to your human paladin friend over

00:30:19.168 --> 00:30:25.901
there and you find the tracks lead up to a large
cluster of bushes that are embedded right in the

00:30:25.901 --> 00:30:36.758
base of the mountain range. They're thorny.
They're dry. It's a small bramble cluster. It's

00:30:36.758 --> 00:30:40.960
about five or so feet up. It's a wide chunk and
you can see bits and pieces of it scattered across

00:30:40.960 --> 00:30:46.797
the edge of the mountain range here. As you get
closer you can see some of the jagged edges of the

00:30:46.797 --> 00:30:50.970
boosh have a faint-- A boosh. The boosh.

00:30:50.970 --> 00:30:54.165
TRAVIS: Are you amused by the boosh?

00:30:54.165 --> 00:31:09.389
MATT: You find the boosh rather amusing. On the
jagged edges of the bush you see faint elements of

00:31:09.389 --> 00:31:13.149
a waxy residue that have been scraped onto some of
the thorns of the brambles.

00:31:13.149 --> 00:31:15.341
LIAM: Probably unrelated.

00:31:15.341 --> 00:31:21.537
MATT: Just beyond you can barely see a dark
recess, about four feet tall and about four feet

00:31:21.537 --> 00:31:24.514
wide, behind the bush, that presses into the
mountain range.

00:31:24.514 --> 00:31:31.676
TRAVIS: The tracks lead to this bush. If you see
just beyond there's a recess in the mountains.

00:31:31.676 --> 00:31:33.517
LAURA: How big is the recess?

00:31:33.517 --> 00:31:36.676
TRAVIS: It's like four-- what is it? How far
about?

00:31:36.676 --> 00:31:40.712
MATT: Four foot wide and four foot tall.

00:31:40.712 --> 00:31:44.248
LAURA: Oh. That's small for a human.

00:31:44.248 --> 00:31:46.106
TRAVIS: Indeed it is.

00:31:46.106 --> 00:31:50.728
LAURA: So I wonder if these creatures who stole
the candles are smaller than humans.

00:31:50.728 --> 00:31:55.023
TRAVIS: My hypothesis exactly.

00:31:55.023 --> 00:31:57.783
TALIESIN: Or they're prone to crawling.

00:31:57.783 --> 00:31:59.087
LAURA: Oh, or that.

00:31:59.087 --> 00:32:02.939
TALIESIN: They could be crawlers. That's some mean
crawlers.

00:32:02.939 --> 00:32:08.357
JENNIFER: Gren-- Grel-- Greldamin?

00:32:08.357 --> 00:32:14.759
LAURA: Greldamine. It's okay, it's a hard name.
Especially for elves.

00:32:14.759 --> 00:32:21.255
(laughter)

00:32:21.255 --> 00:32:23.878
JENNIFER: It looks like you could stand upright in
that hole.

00:32:23.878 --> 00:32:26.135
LAURA: I could.

00:32:26.135 --> 00:32:31.448
JENNIFER: Yes. It's another element we should
factor into our search.

00:32:31.448 --> 00:32:35.472
LAURA: Should I go in? Should we all go in?

00:32:35.472 --> 00:32:37.016
LIAM: You first, little one.

00:32:37.016 --> 00:32:40.653
LAURA: Gladly. Can we move these thorny bushes out
of the way though?

00:32:40.653 --> 00:32:44.459
TRAVIS: Absolutely. I start ripping the dried
brush out of the--

00:32:44.459 --> 00:32:48.183
MATT: The brush is actually not attached to the
ground. It comes and pulls out of the way really

00:32:48.183 --> 00:32:49.445
easily.

00:32:49.445 --> 00:32:51.320
JENNIFER: Does he fall on his butt when he pulls
on it that hard?

00:32:51.320 --> 00:32:55.449
MATT: He almost does. He teeters on one foot as
his sheer show of strength to tear them out

00:32:55.449 --> 00:33:00.559
overcompensates and his armored self, being top
heavy as he is, he stands there and awkwardly

00:33:00.559 --> 00:33:08.808
wobbles in place. And for a moment you see as the
bartender, Wental, swallows deeply out of the

