LAURA: Why do we need to do that?

01:13:38.808 --> 01:13:43.885
LIAM: I don't know. You know, conserving energy,
that kind of thing. Let's go! You want to kick

01:13:43.885 --> 01:13:46.231
ass, I can tell. Little one, let's go.

01:13:46.231 --> 01:13:53.573
JENNIFER: I'm with her. I will now call her Small
and Brave. I'm with Small and Brave. SB for short.

01:13:53.573 --> 01:14:00.471
TALIESIN: I can't do Prayer of Healing while we're
walking though, can I? It's just verbal.

01:14:00.471 --> 01:14:04.271
MATT: Is it the ten minute one? You have to sit
still for ten minutes to do it.

01:14:04.271 --> 01:14:15.582
TALIESIN: Ten minutes to heal everybody up a bit.
So that's 2d8 plus my spellcasting ability

01:14:15.582 --> 01:14:17.034
modifier?

01:14:17.034 --> 01:14:19.491
TRAVIS: That's not long enough for hit dice and
stuff though?

01:14:19.491 --> 01:14:21.458
MATT: So roll 2d8 plus your wisdom modifier.

01:14:21.458 --> 01:14:22.694
TALIESIN: Oh my god, really?

01:14:22.694 --> 01:14:24.611
MATT: Double ones?

01:14:24.611 --> 01:14:25.711
TALIESIN: Yep.

01:14:25.711 --> 01:14:31.170
TRAVIS: You gave the golden snitch away, Taliesin.
This is the beginning of the end.

01:14:31.170 --> 01:14:32.206
LAURA: Did he really?

01:14:32.206 --> 01:14:33.725
LIAM: He tossed it at the DM.

01:14:33.725 --> 01:14:39.236
TALIESIN: So that's nine points of healing to
everybody.

01:14:39.236 --> 01:14:41.463
MATT: Still good. All of you guys heal nine
points. That's not bad.

01:14:41.463 --> 01:14:48.057
JENNIFER: Okay, so we already added the five, but
we don't get the five?

01:14:48.057 --> 01:14:51.158
MATT: Nine on top of that.

01:14:51.158 --> 01:14:53.266
JENNIFER: Nine more on top of the five? Okay.

01:14:53.266 --> 01:15:01.028
MATT: As Bundle finishes the Prayer of Healing and
you all feel your wounds begin to close and stitch

01:15:01.028 --> 01:15:04.988
themselves together, you see a little bit of
movement at the edge of the banks. Between the

01:15:04.988 --> 01:15:12.903
rock that had plummeted into it, you watch as a
tiny hand-- Climbing out of the water you see a

01:15:12.903 --> 01:15:16.730
very bloodied, smashed, one eye swollen kobold.

01:15:16.730 --> 01:15:20.009
LAURA: Can I use Firebolt at it?

01:15:20.009 --> 01:15:25.391
TRAVIS: No! Don't you want to ask maybe what they
were doing down here, or what their plans might

01:15:25.391 --> 01:15:26.490
be?

01:15:26.490 --> 01:15:28.733
LAURA: Oh, I mean sure, if that sounds good to
you!

01:15:28.733 --> 01:15:30.576
TRAVIS: I think it might be wise.

01:15:30.576 --> 01:15:32.771
LAURA: I'm a rage monster. I just like to kill
things!

01:15:32.771 --> 01:15:34.319
TRAVIS: I know that about you.

01:15:34.319 --> 01:15:36.260
JENNIFER: That's why she's my new best friend.

01:15:36.260 --> 01:15:37.727
LAURA: Go for it.

01:15:37.727 --> 01:15:42.420
TRAVIS: Can I go over and pick it up by the back
of the neck?

01:15:42.420 --> 01:15:43.661
MATT: (squeals)

01:15:43.661 --> 01:15:48.168
TRAVIS: Hello, friend. Before I let one of these
fine people--

01:15:48.168 --> 01:15:52.266
MATT: As he's scrambling right now, looking up at
the candle which is currently out because of the

01:15:52.266 --> 01:15:55.674
waterlogged, it's like (whimpers).

01:15:55.674 --> 01:16:02.741
TRAVIS: I know, a very sad face. Before one of
these fine people sends you to your maker, what

01:16:02.741 --> 01:16:04.031
were you doing in here?

01:16:04.031 --> 01:16:10.378
MATT: "Okay. Just, you friend, right? I work,
help!"

01:16:10.378 --> 01:16:14.266
TRAVIS: Yes, friend. Much more work for you,
friend.

01:16:14.266 --> 01:16:15.661
MATT: "Reeksus."

01:16:15.661 --> 01:16:17.498
TRAVIS: Wicksis.

01:16:17.498 --> 01:16:19.073
MATT: "Reeksus."

01:16:19.073 --> 01:16:20.325
TRAVIS: Reeksus.

01:16:20.325 --> 01:16:23.633
LAURA: You understand what he's saying? Because I
can't tell at all.

01:16:23.633 --> 01:16:36.200
MATT: "We sent by great King Togwaggle. Togwaggle
send us to make bigger booms! Make better tunnels

01:16:36.200 --> 01:16:38.207
"to people town!"

01:16:38.207 --> 01:16:42.352
TRAVIS: Yes, I am aware of people town.

01:16:42.352 --> 01:16:46.437
MATT: "King Togwaggle greatest, best of all
kobolds!"

01:16:46.437 --> 01:16:52.101
LIAM: How are those tunnels coming? You've made
them, or making them?

01:16:52.101 --> 01:16:59.009
MATT: "We made and make more, by the glory of
Rakanishu and King Togwaggle."

01:16:59.009 --> 01:17:02.708
TRAVIS: King Togwaggle, is he here with you now,
close by?

01:17:02.708 --> 01:17:06.421
MATT: He looks back towards the closed door.

01:17:06.421 --> 01:17:09.677
TRAVIS: Back that way?

01:17:09.677 --> 01:17:12.612
LAURA: Does the king have all of our candles?

01:17:12.612 --> 01:17:14.159
MATT: "Lots of candles."

01:17:14.159 --> 01:17:17.179
LAURA: Lots of candles. We should talk to him.

01:17:17.179 --> 01:17:20.020
JENNIFER: How many people are with the king?

01:17:20.020 --> 01:17:24.876
MATT: "People? No people."

01:17:24.876 --> 01:17:28.020
JENNIFER: Sorry, how many of your kind are with
the king?

01:17:28.020 --> 01:17:31.959
MATT: "King is not very kind either, but is good
king!"

01:17:31.959 --> 01:17:35.331
JENNIFER: Are there many kobolds with the king?

01:17:35.331 --> 01:17:36.871
MATT: "There is a few."

01:17:36.871 --> 01:17:40.047
JENNIFER: More than there were here?

01:17:40.047 --> 01:17:43.064
MATT: "Depends on the time of day."

01:17:43.064 --> 01:17:45.216
LAURA: What about now?

01:17:45.216 --> 01:17:47.507
MATT: "I don't know, we've been away for a
while."

01:17:47.507 --> 01:17:55.520
JENNIFER: When do you eat? When do the kobold
eat?

01:17:55.520 --> 01:17:57.302
MATT: "When there is food."

01:17:57.302 --> 01:17:59.227
LAURA: I like him. Can we keep him?

01:17:59.227 --> 01:18:01.726
TRAVIS: And what would we do with him?

01:18:01.726 --> 01:18:03.135
MATT: "Do you have food to eat?"

01:18:03.135 --> 01:18:08.304
JENNIFER: Do all the kobold eat together?

01:18:08.304 --> 01:18:10.536
LAURA: I pull out some beef jerky and hand it to
him.

01:18:10.536 --> 01:18:11.915
MATT: (messy chewing)

01:18:11.915 --> 01:18:22.773
JENNIFER: There's more where that came from if you
answer the question. Are there more than those of

01:18:22.773 --> 01:18:26.242
us you see here of the kobold?

01:18:26.242 --> 01:18:33.045
MATT: "There are, but scattered. Dangerous
tunnels, find dangerous things. Wander. Avoid

01:18:33.045 --> 01:18:34.674
"them! We do."

01:18:34.674 --> 01:18:40.877
TRAVIS: Quazi, do you think maybe you could
convince him to show us safe passage?

01:18:40.877 --> 01:18:46.809
LIAM: Safe passage, convince him? Oh, yes. Bring
closer.

01:18:46.809 --> 01:18:50.296
MATT: (squeals) And you catch him as he throws
him.

01:18:50.296 --> 01:18:54.793
LIAM: Your hands, what I like about them is
they're so little (bones snapping).

01:18:54.793 --> 01:19:00.731
MATT: (yelps) Make an intimidation check. With
advantage for breaking his hands.

01:19:00.731 --> 01:19:08.153
LIAM: That's a 17.

01:19:08.153 --> 01:19:11.449
MATT: (screams and sobs)

01:19:11.449 --> 01:19:14.942
LIAM: Okay, I can do this to you five more times.

01:19:14.942 --> 01:19:16.761
MATT: "No, I only have two hands!"

01:19:16.761 --> 01:19:28.123
LIAM: I can play this game all night long, little
man. So we need to get inside. We need to be, you

01:19:28.123 --> 01:19:34.413
know, alive and not getting killed, so we would
like to keep you. She has lots of beef jerky, we

01:19:34.413 --> 01:19:38.087
could feed you. But we can't have any, what did
you call these?

01:19:38.087 --> 01:19:44.536
MATT: "Boom booms. Okay, I show you. I show you!
Don't break! No more arms left to break."

01:19:44.536 --> 01:19:47.510
LAURA: Aw, heal him, please? His poor hands!

01:19:47.510 --> 01:19:53.155
LIAM: Well let him earn it first, you know? Maybe,
20 minutes we're still alive, you have healed hand

01:19:53.155 --> 01:19:54.490
and more meat.

01:19:54.490 --> 01:19:56.941
MATT: "Okay. Put me down?"

01:19:56.941 --> 01:19:58.418
LIAM: I'm not holding you.

01:19:58.418 --> 01:19:59.585
TRAVIS: Yes, you are.

01:19:59.585 --> 01:20:05.509
LIAM: You gave him to me? I like this guy. Pat pat
pat.

01:20:05.509 --> 01:20:10.246
MATT: In the rush of combat, you didn't realize
that you were clutching him the whole time.

01:20:10.246 --> 01:20:15.191
LIAM: Well, I went like this. I thought you were
holding him. You know, Dungeons &amp; Dragons is funny

01:20:15.191 --> 01:20:22.270
thing. Your mind's different from my mind. Who
knows what we're seeing? I drop his ass on

01:20:22.270 --> 01:20:23.457
ground.

01:20:23.457 --> 01:20:25.717
MATT: "We need to go through door."

01:20:25.717 --> 01:20:28.193
JENNIFER: Should we secure him?

01:20:28.193 --> 01:20:30.207
LAURA: If you want.

01:20:30.207 --> 01:20:31.299
TALIESIN: We've got rope.

01:20:31.299 --> 01:20:36.745
TRAVIS: Just so we make sure you don't break your
other hand, she's going to make sure that you're

01:20:36.745 --> 01:20:38.284
secure.

01:20:38.284 --> 01:20:40.264
MATT: "Okay."

01:20:40.264 --> 01:20:42.501
JENNIFER: Do I need to roll something for that?

01:20:42.501 --> 01:20:45.759
MATT: No, easy enough. He waits for you-- You have
rope on you?

01:20:45.759 --> 01:20:47.004
JENNIFER: I do, I have rope.

01:20:47.004 --> 01:20:49.881
MATT: Okay, so you go ahead and you bind him up
and you have a little leash that you're holding

01:20:49.881 --> 01:20:52.518
him by. And he's like, "Okay. To the door."

01:20:52.518 --> 01:20:55.473
JENNIFER: Can I pass her the leash since he's her
pet?

01:20:55.473 --> 01:21:02.574
MATT: "Oh. Pet?" Greldamine.

01:21:02.574 --> 01:21:03.926
LAURA: What?

01:21:03.926 --> 01:21:06.565
MATT: You're having a kobold's leash handed to
you.

01:21:06.565 --> 01:21:08.510
JENNIFER: Can I pass him your leash? Would you
like to have him as a pet?

01:21:08.510 --> 01:21:10.760
LAURA: Oh, well, all right.

01:21:10.760 --> 01:21:14.665
MATT: Broken, jagged teeth, spittle drooling
down.

01:21:14.665 --> 01:21:19.133
LAURA: I don't think he's much of a pet. He's more
of a companion.

01:21:19.133 --> 01:21:22.183
MATT: "Could you light the candle?"

01:21:22.183 --> 01:21:24.280
LAURA: I will in a little bit.

01:21:24.280 --> 01:21:26.754
MATT: (whines)

01:21:26.754 --> 01:21:29.283
JENNIFER: Hearts next to it.

01:21:29.283 --> 01:21:31.196
LAURA: What's your name?

01:21:31.196 --> 01:21:33.451
MATT: "Reeksus."

01:21:33.451 --> 01:21:36.083
LAURA: Reeksus. You got it.

01:21:36.083 --> 01:21:40.260
MATT: "Open door!"

01:21:40.260 --> 01:21:41.520
TRAVIS: Through the door then.

01:21:41.520 --> 01:21:46.493
LIAM: And I kick him really hard in the ass. Lead
the way.

01:21:46.493 --> 01:21:49.211
MATT: The door is closed.

01:21:49.211 --> 01:21:50.278
LIAM: Lead the way.

01:21:50.278 --> 01:21:52.642
MATT: "I'm bound! You made me put rope on it!"

01:21:52.642 --> 01:21:54.977
TRAVIS: Is there a latch, a door knob?

01:21:54.977 --> 01:21:58.396
MATT: There is a handle latch and it looks like
there is a lock mechanism to it.

01:21:58.396 --> 01:22:00.780
TRAVIS: Hmm, a lock.

01:22:00.780 --> 01:22:02.430
JENNIFER: Whose purview is this?

01:22:02.430 --> 01:22:05.618
LIAM: That's you. You take look. Make sure it does
not explode on you.

01:22:05.618 --> 01:22:08.786
JENNIFER: I don't see any wicks. I don't see
anything explosive.

01:22:08.786 --> 01:22:12.054
MATT: Make an investigation check if you want to
check for traps.

01:22:12.054 --> 01:22:19.123
JENNIFER: Oh! 25.

01:22:19.123 --> 01:22:22.339
TALIESIN: What did you roll? Well, she rolled a
20.

01:22:22.339 --> 01:22:25.404
LAURA: That's important.

01:22:25.404 --> 01:22:30.708
MATT: Very nice. It's a lock mechanism. A
relatively simple lock. It is not trapped. So, you

01:22:30.708 --> 01:22:34.551
could easily undo this with your thieves' tools.

01:22:34.551 --> 01:22:37.126
JENNIFER: So I do something so I can do that?

01:22:37.126 --> 01:22:41.841
MATT: Yep, so you roll another d20, and then add
your proficiency modifier and your dexterity

01:22:41.841 --> 01:22:43.154
modifier.

01:22:43.154 --> 01:22:46.845
LIAM: This plus this, so plus eight to what you
roll.

01:22:46.845 --> 01:22:49.002
JENNIFER: So that is 14.

01:22:49.002 --> 01:22:57.576
MATT: Easy enough. The door unlocks, opens a bit,
and beyond that is a tunnel of darkness. An

01:22:57.576 --> 01:23:01.708
interesting smell hits you as you open it though.
Whereas inside here you have that damp,

01:23:01.708 --> 01:23:06.781
hard-water, Pirates of the Caribbean ride smell
that's in the water chamber, beyond that as the

01:23:06.781 --> 01:23:16.752
door opens this musty, almost mildewed smell hits
you. It's earthy, it's fresh, it's natural, but

01:23:16.752 --> 01:23:20.544
it's definitely an underground, familiar smell.

01:23:20.544 --> 01:23:23.729
JENNIFER: Why can we never encounter a field of
flowers?

01:23:23.729 --> 01:23:29.993
LAURA: Should I light up a rock again?

01:23:29.993 --> 01:23:37.594
TALIESIN: Oh, I can do it. So I pick up a rock and
light it up, and toss it in front of us. Just keep

01:23:37.594 --> 01:23:40.637
kicking it down.

01:23:40.637 --> 01:23:44.885
MATT: It lights up the chamber as it goes, and you
continue to walk and kick it as you push forward.

01:23:44.885 --> 01:23:52.894
The walls begin to slowly glow the further in you
go. You begin to notice that, aside from a few

01:23:52.894 --> 01:23:57.939
small crystalline areas, there are heavy bits of
fungus that are beginning to appear along these

01:23:57.939 --> 01:24:04.011
chambers. Glowing green, orange, blue mushrooms
and clusters of fungal matter that are beginning

01:24:04.011 --> 01:24:09.084
to give this faint luminescence to the interior of
the chamber. And you now very much understand

01:24:09.084 --> 01:24:17.020
where the smell was coming from. As you begin to
curve around the right side of it, the tunnel

01:24:17.020 --> 01:24:22.400
widens a little broader to about 15 feet wide. The
mushrooms begin to get larger and larger, some of

01:24:22.400 --> 01:24:27.423
them four feet tall or bigger. You can see large
pillar stalactites and stalagmites are meeting in

01:24:27.423 --> 01:24:31.043
the center where they give their own little
offshoots of fungus. But some of these are getting

01:24:31.043 --> 01:24:37.377
very big and the pathways are getting a little
narrow to move past until, as you turn around one

01:24:37.377 --> 01:24:42.508
of the right bends, the fungus is pushed around to
the point where it's a very narrow passage to push

01:24:42.508 --> 01:24:44.241
through these fungal forests.

01:24:44.241 --> 01:24:46.611
LIAM: I don't like mushrooms.

01:24:46.611 --> 01:24:48.601
LAURA: They're quite tasty, actually.

01:24:48.601 --> 01:24:51.629
TALIESIN: Could make a glowing salad of some
kind.

01:24:51.629 --> 01:24:53.470
LAURA: Ooh, yeah. Hey, Reeksus.

01:24:53.470 --> 01:24:55.419
MATT: "Yeah?"

01:24:55.419 --> 01:25:00.642
LAURA: I give him a little bit of beef jerky.
Okay. Do you want to go in front of us and lead

01:25:00.642 --> 01:25:02.468
the way to your king?

01:25:02.468 --> 01:25:12.756
MATT: "Okay." And he carefully turns to his side
and thins up and slowly-- with disadvantage

01:25:12.756 --> 01:25:19.213
because he's bound-- still effectively manages to
squiggle his way between the small path. And you

01:25:19.213 --> 01:25:25.477
can see he knows it pretty well, through the small
cluster of dense tall fungus safely to the other

01:25:25.477 --> 01:25:26.698
side.

01:25:26.698 --> 01:25:28.275
LAURA: Is it bad to touch it?

01:25:28.275 --> 01:25:30.511
MATT: "I would not recommend it."

01:25:30.511 --> 01:25:35.720
LIAM: And the rope is still trailing from him?

01:25:35.720 --> 01:25:40.137
MATT: Yeah, it's 30 feet of slack rope. It's on
the ground over there.

01:25:40.137 --> 01:25:41.696
TRAVIS: If only we had some fire.

01:25:41.696 --> 01:25:51.790
LAURA: Oh. Do you want me to set these on fire?
Because I have some. I mean, is it safe to burn?

01:25:51.790 --> 01:25:59.418
What if it sets off a poison when they're on fire?
I've heard that burning mushrooms could get you,

01:25:59.418 --> 01:26:01.949
you know--

01:26:01.949 --> 01:26:03.830
TRAVIS: &lt;i&gt;Eating&lt;/i&gt; mushrooms.

01:26:03.830 --> 01:26:05.236
LAURA: Oh, it's not fumes?

01:26:05.236 --> 01:26:06.734
TALIESIN, LIAM and TRAVIS: No.

01:26:06.734 --> 01:26:16.388
LAURA: Oh! I wouldn't know. They don't allow that
kind of stuff at mage school. Okay! I'm going to

01:26:16.388 --> 01:26:20.866
go through! Wait, am I going to burn it? I'm going
to get to the other side and then I'm going to try

01:26:20.866 --> 01:26:26.720
to burn it. I don't want to burn Reeks. Okay. I go
to the other side.

01:26:26.720 --> 01:26:30.683
MATT: Okay. Go ahead and make a straight dexterity
check, please.

01:26:30.683 --> 01:26:41.949
LAURA: All right. Woo-hoo! What is that, 18 or 19?
18 plus dexterity. 21.

01:26:41.949 --> 01:26:45.992
MATT: Following suit, you deftly follow the same
pattern and come out the other side, not even

01:26:45.992 --> 01:26:54.902
touching any of the fungus with either side of your
armored shoulder pauldrons. Your mantle, I guess

01:26:54.902 --> 01:26:56.292
it would be.

01:26:56.292 --> 01:27:00.013
LAURA: Should I try to burn them now? What do you
guys think?

01:27:00.013 --> 01:27:04.705
LIAM: Depends on what we think biggest threat is.
Touching mushroom, breathing mushroom?

01:27:04.705 --> 01:27:12.634
JENNIFER: Should we test it first? Touch it to
test it to see if it affects us?

01:27:12.634 --> 01:27:16.934
TRAVIS: I'm afraid they might release spores and
then become airborne which is why I only recommend

01:27:16.934 --> 01:27:18.356
trying to burn it first.

01:27:18.356 --> 01:27:21.931
JENNIFER: That would release a lot of spores.

01:27:21.931 --> 01:27:25.372
LIAM: How far away can you cast that shit from?

01:27:25.372 --> 01:27:31.828
LAURA: It's ranged about eight. I don't know what
that means.

01:27:31.828 --> 01:27:34.011
MATT: Is this Burning Hands?

01:27:34.011 --> 01:27:35.758
LAURA: No, Fire Bolt.

01:27:35.758 --> 01:27:39.714
MATT: Oh, Fire Bolt? Oh, it's a pretty decent
range. Just a single hit, yeah.

01:27:39.714 --> 01:27:44.522
LIAM: What if we all back up to our different
sides, yeah? Get back as far as you can and we'll

01:27:44.522 --> 01:27:47.777
get way the fuck back. See what happens.

01:27:47.777 --> 01:27:50.806
LAURA: And then I'll hit it because I can do
cantrips a lot, right?

01:27:50.806 --> 01:27:52.552
MATT: Cantrips you can do as many times as you
want.

01:27:52.552 --> 01:27:54.394
LAURA: Fuck-- I mean heck yeah! I'm going to do--

01:27:54.394 --> 01:27:57.452
TRAVIS: They don't let cursing happen in mage
school either?

01:27:57.452 --> 01:27:59.998
LAURA: They don't curse in mage school. I'm sorry
about that.

01:27:59.998 --> 01:28:01.948
MATT: Yeah, they're real tough on that in
Dalaran.

01:28:01.948 --> 01:28:03.756
LAURA: They smack your hands. I'll tell you that
much.

01:28:03.756 --> 01:28:09.295
MATT: They wouldn't tell you but Madame had a
potty mouth.

01:28:09.295 --> 01:28:17.448
LAURA: I'm going to cast Fire Bolt at the
mushrooms. That gives me 2d10 fire damage.

01:28:17.448 --> 01:28:22.864
MATT: Yes, even with a singular bolt, the
mushroom's pretty big and it's not moving. It's

01:28:22.864 --> 01:28:27.578
pretty easy to hit. You hit the first one a while
away and as it impacts you watch as the flames

01:28:27.578 --> 01:28:35.300
burn up. Immediately the strange, subtle squeaking
sound releases as it shakes and shimmies. And you

01:28:35.300 --> 01:28:41.388
watch as spores filter out and then ignite from
the nearby flames that immediately destroy the

01:28:41.388 --> 01:28:45.857
cloud before it can emerge. And the fungus slowly
withers and crumples over.

01:28:45.857 --> 01:28:49.634
LAURA: Okay, good! I do the same thing on all of
the mushrooms that are along the path.

01:28:49.634 --> 01:28:58.323
MATT: Okay. One by one you create this pathway,
destroying the fungus on the opposite side. Are

01:28:58.323 --> 01:28:59.978
you still holding the rope?

01:28:59.978 --> 01:29:01.219
LAURA: Yes.

01:29:01.219 --> 01:29:03.431
MATT: Okay. As the flames begin--

01:29:03.431 --> 01:29:06.363
LAURA: But I went through, remember? I went
through and I'm holding the rope on my side.

01:29:06.363 --> 01:29:10.309
MATT: Right. So as you're destroying these the
rope pulls a little taut to your side as you begin

01:29:10.309 --> 01:29:14.412
clearing the path. And you look over and you can
see your friend is peeking around a rock. You can

01:29:14.412 --> 01:29:18.723
see this glow on the other side of a boulder
around the bend where he's looking over and looks

01:29:18.723 --> 01:29:20.652
back at you and is like--

01:29:20.652 --> 01:29:21.892
LAURA: What?

01:29:21.892 --> 01:29:23.182
MATT: (mutters)

01:29:23.182 --> 01:29:24.249
LAURA: Hold on.

01:29:24.249 --> 01:29:28.916
MATT: "Okay." The rest of you guys, there is a
path wide enough to follow through.

01:29:28.916 --> 01:29:30.601
TRAVIS: We join.

01:29:30.601 --> 01:29:32.532
LAURA: They're coming? Okay, I go over to Reek.

01:29:32.532 --> 01:29:39.168
MATT: As you guys approach you can see the small
flickering of light shift suddenly and a dark

01:29:39.168 --> 01:29:46.737
shape of a figure whips around from behind the
rock. You see a flash of cloth that floats open

01:29:46.737 --> 01:29:52.472
and then drifts down to the side as an arm
uncurls. You can see immediately wide-shouldered,

01:29:52.472 --> 01:29:59.133
a broad long trench coat that swings open to one
side, a clawed, familiar, slightly furred hand

01:29:59.133 --> 01:30:06.094
holding it open as a brownish hat, wide-brimmed,
appears with its candle placed on top of the brim.

01:30:06.094 --> 01:30:10.913
You see another kobold standing there looking at
your tied-up friend and the rest of you. And he

01:30:10.913 --> 01:30:20.585
goes, "Hey! Hey! Want to buy a fungus?" As you
look on the inside of the cloak you can see these

01:30:20.585 --> 01:30:28.478
little patchwork pouches of different gathered
mushrooms, orange, green and blue. "I sell, good

01:30:28.478 --> 01:30:30.263
"price. Come. Buy."

01:30:30.263 --> 01:30:32.201
TALIESIN: Well--

01:30:32.201 --> 01:30:34.148
LAURA: Well, what do they do?

01:30:34.148 --> 01:30:38.750
MATT: "Taste good! Ugh. Bad. Good bad. Fun!"

01:30:38.750 --> 01:30:41.129
LAURA: I don't understand what he just told me.

01:30:41.129 --> 01:30:45.162
LIAM: I mean, to begin with you're not alarmed by
us being here in the first place?

01:30:45.162 --> 01:30:47.431
MATT: "I need to make money."

01:30:47.431 --> 01:30:54.314
TALIESIN: Let's not look a gift horse in the
mouth. A gift rat. Orange?

01:30:54.314 --> 01:31:01.579
MATT: "Orange fungus. Slight citrus-y taste. Weird
fuzzy sensation. 40 gold."

01:31:01.579 --> 01:31:05.332
TALIESIN: And the other two were--

01:31:05.332 --> 01:31:06.762
TRAVIS: What about blue?

01:31:06.762 --> 01:31:11.190
MATT: "Blue fungus. 30 gold. Make for good
digestion tract."

01:31:11.190 --> 01:31:13.485
TRAVIS: I'll take the blue one.

01:31:13.485 --> 01:31:15.111
LAURA: You have that much gold?

01:31:15.111 --> 01:31:16.458
TRAVIS: Yeah.

01:31:16.458 --> 01:31:18.549
MATT: You now have a helping of blue fungus.

01:31:18.549 --> 01:31:20.599
TALIESIN: What's the third?

01:31:20.599 --> 01:31:28.318
MATT: "Green fungus! 25 gold. More of the onion of
fungus family."

01:31:28.318 --> 01:31:30.160
LAURA: That's a good topping.

01:31:30.160 --> 01:31:31.636
MATT: "Yeah!"

01:31:31.636 --> 01:31:37.233
LIAM: I grab rope that is holding Reekcheeks and
bring him over. "You know this one?"

01:31:37.233 --> 01:31:44.203
MATT: "He is strange one. Don't like him. I
don't-- kobolds stay away."

01:31:44.203 --> 01:31:45.533
LIAM: Is he problem?

01:31:45.533 --> 01:31:48.399
MATT: (whispering) "I don't know."

01:31:48.399 --> 01:31:50.105
LAURA: You be nice to him!

01:31:50.105 --> 01:31:53.383
TRAVIS: It's the-- they're real--

01:31:53.383 --> 01:31:54.513
LIAM: I punch him in the eye.

01:31:54.513 --> 01:31:55.777
MATT: (cry of pain)

01:31:55.777 --> 01:31:57.505
TALIESIN: You only live once. Orange.

01:31:57.505 --> 01:31:59.268
LIAM: You've got to keep them in line with tough
love.

01:31:59.268 --> 01:32:01.252
TALIESIN: I take the orange.

01:32:01.252 --> 01:32:02.265
MATT: All righty.

01:32:02.265 --> 01:32:04.462
TRAVIS: Do I know anything about this blue fungus?

01:32:04.462 --> 01:32:05.835
MATT: Make a medicine check.

01:32:05.835 --> 01:32:08.200
LAURA: It's good for digestion I hear.

01:32:08.200 --> 01:32:09.305
TRAVIS: 16.

01:32:09.305 --> 01:32:10.517
MATT: 16, okay.

01:32:10.517 --> 01:32:13.221
TALIESIN: Oh, 20.

01:32:13.221 --> 01:32:24.971
MATT: Okay. So eating this fungus has a chance of
poisoning you, but also has the opportunity to

01:32:24.971 --> 01:32:29.869
heighten your senses and perceptive capabilities
for a short time.

01:32:29.869 --> 01:32:31.912
LAURA: Ooh, it's a gamble.

01:32:31.912 --> 01:32:34.168
TALIESIN: How about mine?

01:32:34.168 --> 01:32:36.193
MATT: So that's the orange one, you got the--

01:32:36.193 --> 01:32:37.429
TALIESIN: I have the orange.

01:32:37.429 --> 01:32:38.418
MATT: You've got the orange.

01:32:38.418 --> 01:32:39.306
LAURA: Yeah, he got the blue.

01:32:39.306 --> 01:32:43.101
MATT: He got the blue, sorry, yeah. So the blue
one has a faint possibility of poisoning you.

01:32:43.101 --> 01:32:48.699
Sorry, you're the blue. The orange one is the one
you got. So you get the heightened senses, yours

01:32:48.699 --> 01:32:52.698
has a chance of poisoning you as well and or has
the possibility of healing some hit points.

01:32:52.698 --> 01:32:55.661
TALIESIN: Down the hatch.

01:32:55.661 --> 01:32:58.811
MATT: All right, both of you make constitution
saving throws.

01:32:58.811 --> 01:33:00.538
LIAM: Give it to Mikey, he'll try anything.

01:33:00.538 --> 01:33:05.294
TRAVIS: Now, because you're next to me I have Aura
of Protection which is plus two to saves?

01:33:05.294 --> 01:33:06.517
MATT: Yeah, it would.

01:33:06.517 --> 01:33:09.946
TALIESIN: Oh, that helps because my constitution's
really low.

01:33:09.946 --> 01:33:13.812
TRAVIS: Yes! 21.

01:33:13.812 --> 01:33:15.133
TALIESIN: Eight.

01:33:15.133 --> 01:33:18.043
MATT: Okay, so you're poisoned for the next hour.

01:33:18.043 --> 01:33:26.016
The poisoned status means all of your
attacks are at disadvantage and your ability

01:33:26.016 --> 01:33:34.463
checks are at disadvantage as well. So you have
advantage on all perception and investigation

01:33:34.463 --> 01:33:36.452
checks for the next hour.

01:33:36.452 --> 01:33:38.391
LIAM: Everything is crystal clear.

01:33:38.391 --> 01:33:42.648
MATT: Yeah, your eyes dilate suddenly and I know
kung-fu.

01:33:42.648 --> 01:33:44.362
TRAVIS: Yeah! Show me.

01:33:44.362 --> 01:33:48.206
MATT: Bundle, you heal six hit points.

01:33:48.206 --> 01:33:50.946
TALIESIN: I heal six?

01:33:50.946 --> 01:33:52.544
LAURA: Ooh, at least it healed you while it
poisoned you.

01:33:52.544 --> 01:33:57.174
TALIESIN: I'm also going to cast Lesser
Restoration and make the poison go away.

01:33:57.174 --> 01:34:04.941
MATT: Okay. So the poison vanishes from your
system at which point the kobold, "Mushhuckster

01:34:04.941 --> 01:34:10.988
"Max thanks you. Now off to find new ventures!"
Pulls the cloak in front of his head and darts

01:34:10.988 --> 01:34:15.391
away on little ninja feet. Back through the
mushrooms and vanishes into darkness.

01:34:15.391 --> 01:34:19.706
TALIESIN: It's weird he's selling mushrooms to
random people in caverns like that.

01:34:19.706 --> 01:34:21.811
TRAVIS: I highly recommend the blue fungus.

01:34:21.811 --> 01:34:28.035
LIAM: In another life, I would have hit that guy
before he said a single word. I would have dropped

01:34:28.035 --> 01:34:30.294
his ass.

01:34:30.294 --> 01:34:32.139
TRAVIS: Somehow I know that to be true about you.

01:34:32.139 --> 01:34:38.494
MATT: At this point you hear a strange guttural
growl from the path that you were traveling near a

01:34:38.494 --> 01:34:43.254
pillar of stone encased in mushrooms as from
around one back of it you see a shape of a large,

01:34:43.254 --> 01:34:51.729
hunched, bestial dwarf ape-like creature standing
at about six and a half feet tall as its long arms

01:34:51.729 --> 01:34:57.637
drag on the ground. It's drooling down its own
chest. You've experienced, most of you in particular,

01:34:57.637 --> 01:35:05.302
this is a trogg, a large subterranean creature,
but this trogg is acting strange. It's giggling to

01:35:05.302 --> 01:35:11.370
itself. (deep laughter) Holds the pillar and grabs
some mushroom and scarfs it.

01:35:11.370 --> 01:35:12.121
LAURA: Oh no.

01:35:12.121 --> 01:35:13.487
JENNIFER: Here we go.

01:35:13.487 --> 01:35:23.320
MATT: (grunts) And he starts walking around the
edge, looks around the edge right to you, "It's

01:35:23.320 --> 01:35:25.144
"real?"

01:35:25.144 --> 01:35:28.594
TALIESIN, JENNIFER, and LAURA: No!

01:35:28.594 --> 01:35:30.831
MATT: Make a persuasion check.

01:35:30.831 --> 01:35:41.841
TALIESIN: Come on! Natural 20! About fucking time!
There we are! No!

01:35:41.841 --> 01:35:52.449
MATT: "Too weird! I see things!" You see two other
large troggs come from behind going. They're

01:35:52.449 --> 01:36:01.975
tripping balls. One of them is currently clutching
a long staff of purple and gold inlay and is

01:36:01.975 --> 01:36:06.311
gnawing on it like a large lollipop. You can't see
the top because it's jammed in his mouth. They're

01:36:06.311 --> 01:36:09.485
all looking at you going (laughing).

01:36:09.485 --> 01:36:14.162
TALIESIN: I'm going to use Thaumaturgy to make us
all look really fuzzy, in and out, if I can do

01:36:14.162 --> 01:36:15.142
that.

01:36:15.142 --> 01:36:16.251
MATT: You may.

01:36:16.251 --> 01:36:17.865
TALIESIN: Ooh!

01:36:17.865 --> 01:36:35.199
MATT: No. Okay! They all stand there and watch.
(groaning) One of them picks his nose slowly.

01:36:35.199 --> 01:36:38.221
TALIESIN: I hadn't thought this through.

01:36:38.221 --> 01:36:42.245
LAURA: I use Prestidigitation and create light
flares around him.

01:36:42.245 --> 01:36:47.200
MATT: One elbows one in the chin, the guy who was
holding the staff, he elbows him the chest.

01:36:47.200 --> 01:36:55.553
(gagging) Pulls it out. You can see on the top of
the staff, it has these awesome, pointed purple

01:36:55.553 --> 01:37:02.829
stones, three of them in a triangular pattern that
float, locked into place. (licking) Jams it back

01:37:02.829 --> 01:37:04.918
in his mouth and begins chewing on it again.

01:37:04.918 --> 01:37:12.282
TALIESIN: Can I make the staff look like it's made
of snakes or something? Can I Thaumaturgy?

01:37:12.282 --> 01:37:15.870
MATT: Unfortunately, that's an illusion spell.
Thaumaturgy is very simple. It's a very faint

01:37:15.870 --> 01:37:19.917
effect that wouldn't have an effect if they
weren't already tripping balls.

01:37:19.917 --> 01:37:22.049
LAURA: If they're already tripping can we say:
Whoa, why are you holding that snake in your

01:37:22.049 --> 01:37:23.540
hand?

01:37:23.540 --> 01:37:26.873
MATT: Make a persuasion check!

01:37:26.873 --> 01:37:35.010
LAURA: Please! Oh no, 11.

01:37:35.010 --> 01:37:41.488
MATT: 11. He goes (gags). Pulls it out, looks at
it, "Hey, a snake!" and begins trying to bite

01:37:41.488 --> 01:37:44.136
through. You watch as his teeth are breaking on
the metal.

01:37:44.136 --> 01:37:50.740
TRAVIS: I'll cast Command on him and say: drop
that wicked snake!

01:37:50.740 --> 01:37:56.758
MATT: Okay! What's your spell DC?

01:37:56.758 --> 01:37:58.098
TRAVIS: 13.

01:37:58.098 --> 01:38:08.848
MATT: He rolled a 13 minus one. This trogg is not
very wise. Drops it. You see he's putting his

01:38:08.848 --> 01:38:12.734
tongue through his mouth and bits of teeth are
falling out of his lips and bouncing off of his

01:38:12.734 --> 01:38:21.246
belly. (grunts) They're all currently entranced by
the movement and the lights that you've created.

01:38:21.246 --> 01:38:26.578
JENNIFER: I'd love to collect the thing.

01:38:26.578 --> 01:38:30.759
MATT: Make a stealth check to see if you can not
gather their gaze as they're currently entranced

01:38:30.759 --> 01:38:31.837
by this.

01:38:31.837 --> 01:38:34.587
TRAVIS: We're doing our best outside inflatable
people.

01:38:34.587 --> 01:38:35.946
JENNIFER: 21.

01:38:35.946 --> 01:38:43.582
MATT: 21. You slowly, subtly go beneath their
eyeline, slip out, and pull the staff away as

01:38:43.582 --> 01:38:50.710
they're all still (gasping). One of them begins
picking his ear, pulls something out, and eats

01:38:50.710 --> 01:38:51.710
it.

01:38:51.710 --> 01:38:53.341
(groaning)

01:38:53.341 --> 01:38:55.208
LAURA: We should back away slowly.

01:38:55.208 --> 01:38:56.959
MATT: (farts)

01:38:56.959 --> 01:39:00.595
TALIESIN: Oh, slowly. Okay!

01:39:00.595 --> 01:39:04.825
LAURA: Reeks, if we leave them, will you keep
guiding the way?

01:39:04.825 --> 01:39:12.235
MATT: "Behind them? The way is where they came
from."

01:39:12.235 --> 01:39:18.973
TRAVIS: Quazi? Feel like introducing yourself?

01:39:18.973 --> 01:39:32.566
LIAM: Good news, my brothers. We come from both
the future and the past.

01:39:32.566 --> 01:39:35.695
MATT: All three of them (grunt).

01:39:35.695 --> 01:39:40.942
LIAM: Let me tell you. Your fathers are proud of
you.

01:39:40.942 --> 01:39:50.739
MATT: The two on the sides look in to the one in
the center who goes, "You know father?"

01:39:50.739 --> 01:40:02.839
LIAM: I've been this fucked up before. Your
mothers love you and are proud of you!

01:40:02.839 --> 01:40:05.717
MATT: Make a persuasion check.

01:40:05.717 --> 01:40:15.302
LIAM: Persuasion, you said. That's 18.

01:40:15.302 --> 01:40:22.577
MATT: 18? His giant, meaty, fur-covered hands clap
onto your shoulders of your armor and pulls you in

01:40:22.577 --> 01:40:28.212
close. You can smell the horrible trogg breath
billow out across your face. Almost thickens the

01:40:28.212 --> 01:40:33.969
air around you. It smells of rotting meat and a
multitude of terrible memories.

01:40:33.969 --> 01:40:41.580
LIAM: And the deep secret is: You know that I am
you.

01:40:41.580 --> 01:40:52.257
MATT: He releases you and takes a step back and
goes. (sobbing) And starts sobbing openly. The two

01:40:52.257 --> 01:40:56.493
other troggs clap the side of his shoulders and
start sobbing, too. The three of them sit in place

01:40:56.493 --> 01:41:02.566
and start having the most basic of existential
crises you could watch.

01:41:02.566 --> 01:41:05.638
TALIESIN: Slowly making our way around the
existential crisis.

01:41:05.638 --> 01:41:08.923
MATT: The rest of you make a stealth check. You
already made one. The rest of you make a stealth

01:41:08.923 --> 01:41:10.041
check.

01:41:10.041 --> 01:41:18.550
LIAM: Doing inches this way like an arc. And Papa
and Mama don't want you to hurt you! You have to

01:41:18.550 --> 01:41:21.739
love you!

01:41:21.739 --> 01:41:27.980
MATT: You get the sense they're picking up every
third word due to the limits of their language

01:41:27.980 --> 01:41:41.128
comprehension. They're like, (grunting) "Love!
(grunting) Ove! (sobbing) Guh!" They're just

01:41:41.128 --> 01:41:42.867
making guttural noises at this point.

01:41:42.867 --> 01:41:44.117
LIAM: Give into it.

01:41:44.117 --> 01:41:45.557
MATT: Make a stealth check, please.

01:41:45.557 --> 01:41:49.427
LIAM: Oh, that's a 20!

01:41:49.427 --> 01:42:00.793
MATT: As you guys slowly curve around the three
sobbing troggs, staff in hand, you exit through

01:42:00.793 --> 01:42:06.328
the tunnel they had passed through. The fungus
begins to give way as the heat begins to rise

01:42:06.328 --> 01:42:10.902
steadily once you traverse further into this
tunnel. You're holding the staff. As you're

01:42:10.902 --> 01:42:23.529
walking, looking over it, a slow voice beings to
peek in seemingly from nowhere. It says, "Oh,

01:42:23.529 --> 01:42:31.084
"wondrous. Another unworthy soul. I command you to
throw me into a river and be done with it."

01:42:31.084 --> 01:42:37.646
JENNIFER: Hmm. First, you must tell us your
secrets.

01:42:37.646 --> 01:42:42.866
MATT: "I require a wielder who walks the path of
power, fool."

01:42:42.866 --> 01:42:44.695
LAURA: What's it saying?

01:42:44.695 --> 01:42:49.017
JENNIFER: It requires a wielder who walks the path
of power, fool.

01:42:49.017 --> 01:42:50.037
LAURA: Magic?

01:42:50.037 --> 01:42:52.507
JENNIFER: I'm not calling you a fool, it's calling
you a fool. Magic.

01:42:52.507 --> 01:42:55.267
LAURA: I do magic!

01:42:55.267 --> 01:42:57.242
JENNIFER: Take him.

01:42:57.242 --> 01:43:04.985
MATT: As you take the staff, it warms to your
touch. For a moment, there's an awkward silence

01:43:04.985 --> 01:43:08.544
of: did she actually hear anything, or has your
friend been crazy the whole time you've been

01:43:08.544 --> 01:43:09.703
traveling?

01:43:09.703 --> 01:43:11.192
JENNIFER: Both.

01:43:11.192 --> 01:43:23.025
MATT: A voice slowly echoes in, "Ah, you! You have
potential. A withered seed that could blossom into

01:43:23.025 --> 01:43:25.026
"a tyrant of the arcane."

01:43:25.026 --> 01:43:27.786
LAURA: Well, I'm pretty blossomed already, but
okay.

01:43:27.786 --> 01:43:37.501
MATT: "Yes. You will do. I am Aluneth and
together, we will do great things." And that's

01:43:37.501 --> 01:43:39.200
where we're going to take a break.

01:43:39.200 --> 01:43:44.110
TRAVIS: Ooh! You've got sentient weapons in this
thing! The little gems are floating in a

01:43:44.110 --> 01:43:44.860
triangle?

01:43:44.860 --> 01:43:47.481
MATT: They're held aloft by some mystical power.

01:43:47.481 --> 01:43:49.063
LAURA: Fancy!

01:43:49.063 --> 01:43:50.347
MATT: I'll show you pictures of it.

01:43:50.347 --> 01:43:53.900
TRAVIS: Nicely done! Your baptism is going well!

01:43:53.900 --> 01:43:56.785
JENNIFER: Sorry about trying the narrative thing!
I was like: Oh shit!

01:43:56.785 --> 01:44:00.333
MATT: No, it's all good! First time in, you just
figure it out. You're doing great.

01:44:00.333 --> 01:44:03.611
JENNIFER: Oh, there's a wall there!

01:44:03.780 --> 01:44:07.208
MATT: Thank you guys so much. We're going to to go
break. We'll be back in a few minutes. Rest, get

01:44:07.208 --> 01:44:13.675
drinks. We have some fun stuff at the break for
you to watch. You get to check out, if you haven't

01:44:13.675 --> 01:44:18.640
seen it, the song I sing for this expansion.
Pretty sure it's coming up.

01:44:18.640 --> 01:44:21.691
LAURA: Notebooks in the store!

01:44:21.691 --> 01:44:22.802
MATT: Yep!

01:44:22.802 --> 01:44:23.838
JENNIFER: Where's the notebook?

