MATT: "Don't let him know you came."

02:06:39.596 --> 02:06:46.041
LAURA: Okay. Tell you what, Lohkor. Will you hold
his leash, please?

02:06:46.041 --> 02:06:47.572
TRAVIS: Sure!

02:06:47.572 --> 02:06:53.830
LAURA: I'm going to fly! I know exactly how to do
it.

02:06:53.830 --> 02:06:57.732
MATT: You cast it on yourself. It's a
concentration for I believe up to an hour?

02:06:57.732 --> 02:06:59.048
LAURA: Ten minutes!

02:06:59.048 --> 02:07:00.468
MATT: Ten minutes. Even better.

02:07:00.468 --> 02:07:04.083
LAURA: Sure, yeah, I'm going to fly. And I'm going
to try to go over to that little alcove and see

02:07:04.083 --> 02:07:05.235
what happens.

02:07:05.235 --> 02:07:08.461
MATT: All right. So you watch as the tiny gnome
suddenly takes off and begins gliding across the

02:07:08.461 --> 02:07:11.874
roof of this magma area.

02:07:11.874 --> 02:07:14.191
LAURA: And I'm giving the creature a wide berth.

02:07:14.191 --> 02:07:15.945
LIAM: Look, Laura, you're finally doing it.

02:07:15.945 --> 02:07:24.192
MATT: As you're doing it, you watch as the magma
rager stares and tracks her as she goes. And as

02:07:24.192 --> 02:07:29.949
you head across the way, it shifts to the very
edge of the platform, almost tensing at the border

02:07:29.949 --> 02:07:35.285
and watches as you slowly descend towards this
platform. As you come down, make a perception

02:07:35.285 --> 02:07:36.834
check.

02:07:36.834 --> 02:07:41.790
LAURA: 17.

02:07:41.790 --> 02:07:47.387
MATT: Glancing, you look down. Yeah, they are
charred and long dead. The armor appears to be

02:07:47.387 --> 02:07:51.121
burned away. There are a few pieces of equipment
that have lasted okay, although covered in black

02:07:51.121 --> 02:07:55.736
soot. There's a couple of small satchels that are
left there and looks like they were back to back.

02:07:55.736 --> 02:07:59.494
Just hoping for help or trying to find a way off,
and eventually, they expired.

02:07:59.494 --> 02:08:04.871
LAURA: I'm sorry you had a tragic ending. I'm
going to keep flying around them. I don't want to

02:08:04.871 --> 02:08:09.289
touch my feet to the ground, in case something
comes out of the ground. But I'm going to dig

02:08:09.289 --> 02:08:11.508
through all of their shit and see what I can find.

02:08:11.508 --> 02:08:13.198
MATT: Make an investigation check.

02:08:13.198 --> 02:08:17.119
TRAVIS: Wow. One.

02:08:17.119 --> 02:08:23.731
LAURA: Goodbye.

02:08:23.731 --> 02:08:33.938
MATT: Okay. Glancing through, most of it falls
apart as you grasp it. The armor crumples and

02:08:33.938 --> 02:08:39.493
falls apart as you touch the armor. The only thing
that catches your attention because it is the one

02:08:39.493 --> 02:08:44.111
piece of equipment that is shining amongst the
rest, is in one of the sheaths. There is a blade,

02:08:44.111 --> 02:08:49.172
that as you pull it out, it's got this beautifully
wicked metal that curves into a point at the end,

02:08:49.172 --> 02:08:54.659
like a forked point. It's got a bit of an energy
pulse gem in the center of where the hilt is. And

02:08:54.659 --> 02:09:00.719
as you reach over to look at it, it looks pristine
untouched by time. (burps) Pardon me! A little

02:09:00.719 --> 02:09:05.018
effervescent tonight, apparently! The soot wipes
off of it cleanly.

02:09:05.018 --> 02:09:16.488
LAURA: I hold it aloft. I found a weapon. I'll
bring it back over to you guys.

02:09:16.488 --> 02:09:18.030
LIAM: I also talk to you.

02:09:18.030 --> 02:09:24.467
MATT: At this point, Aluneth does whisper and say
"You've already found a weapon. This is of no use

02:09:24.467 --> 02:09:25.419
"to you."

02:09:25.419 --> 02:09:27.589
LAURA: I'm not going to keep it. I'm going to give
it away.

02:09:27.589 --> 02:09:33.829
MATT: "Good. The sooner, the better." Goes silent.
You watch as, coasting over, blade forth, the magma

02:09:33.829 --> 02:09:38.380
rager still tensing against the edge as she flies
overhead.

02:09:38.380 --> 02:09:41.839
LAURA: I wave it towards the creature as I fly by,
but I don't get close enough to really do

02:09:41.839 --> 02:09:43.014
anything.

02:09:43.014 --> 02:09:45.958
MATT: Greldamine finally lands on the ground,
presenting the blade.

02:09:45.958 --> 02:09:47.643
LIAM: What kind of blade? How big is this thing?

02:09:47.643 --> 02:09:50.890
MATT: It's a longsword. It's big for a longsword,
but it does technically act as a longsword.

02:09:50.890 --> 02:09:56.368
LAURA: Which one of you would like this beautiful
blade?

02:09:56.368 --> 02:10:00.594
TRAVIS: I would like to see it.

02:10:00.594 --> 02:10:02.862
LIAM: I would also, but I would do roshambo with
you.

02:10:02.862 --> 02:10:03.750
TRAVIS: Yep.

02:10:03.750 --> 02:10:05.992
LIAM: Okay. Best out of three, or just one time?

02:10:05.992 --> 02:10:07.162
TRAVIS: One time. Throw on four.

02:10:07.162 --> 02:10:10.556
LIAM: On four?! I have intelligence of eight.

02:10:10.556 --> 02:10:12.093
TRAVIS: Throw on three.

02:10:12.093 --> 02:10:13.217
LIAM: Throw on three?

02:10:13.217 --> 02:10:14.317
TRAVIS: Throw on one.

02:10:14.317 --> 02:10:22.362
LIAM: Why are you changing it on me? Let's do it
on two. We go one, two, shoot. Okay? All right.

02:10:22.362 --> 02:10:31.952
One, two, shoot! Oh shit, two papers. We go again.
One, two, shoot! Give me that shit.

02:10:31.952 --> 02:10:36.358
MATT: It's a very fine blade.

02:10:36.358 --> 02:10:39.096
JENNIFER: What's the name of her sword again?

02:10:39.096 --> 02:10:40.362
MATT: Aluneth.

02:10:40.362 --> 02:10:41.768
LAURA: It's a staff.

02:10:41.768 --> 02:10:44.617
JENNIFER: Sorry. Does Aluneth have anything to say
about where we are?

02:10:44.617 --> 02:10:51.343
LAURA: Oh mighty Aluneth, do you have anything to
say about where we are?

02:10:51.343 --> 02:10:53.271
LIAM: You seem very crazy right now.

02:10:53.271 --> 02:10:54.804
LAURA: It talks, I swear.

02:10:54.804 --> 02:11:03.958
MATT: The voice comes back in from the aether. "I
do despise these subterranean regions. I don't

02:11:03.958 --> 02:11:09.426
"recognize where we are. This world has changed
quite a bit since I last walked its surface."

02:11:09.426 --> 02:11:11.732
LAURA: Yes.

02:11:11.732 --> 02:11:14.582
JENNIFER: How long since you walked its surface?

02:11:14.582 --> 02:11:18.462
LAURA: How long since you walked its surface? I
mean, I know, I've heard about Aluneth before.

02:11:18.462 --> 02:11:19.938
It's very ancient.

02:11:19.938 --> 02:11:26.600
MATT: "Of course you have. I don't know,
generations."

02:11:26.600 --> 02:11:28.525
LAURA: Long time.

02:11:28.525 --> 02:11:31.187
TALIESIN: Could you fly over to the--

02:11:31.187 --> 02:11:34.318
MATT: Do you wish to attune to the weapon?

02:11:34.318 --> 02:11:38.021
LIAM: Hell yeah. I am attuned to nothing, so I
will attune to this.

02:11:38.021 --> 02:11:41.166
LAURA: You want me to go over to the collapse?

02:11:41.166 --> 02:11:45.071
TALIESIN: Yeah, lead the creature over to that
section.

02:11:45.071 --> 02:11:51.003
LAURA: Oh, okay! I'm going to fly over to the
collapsed area, because I've still got a little

02:11:51.003 --> 02:11:52.203
time left, right?

02:11:52.203 --> 02:11:54.111
MATT: Okay, so you coast over to the collapsed
area.

02:11:54.111 --> 02:11:57.734
LAURA: And I land. Now what do you want me to do?

02:11:57.734 --> 02:12:00.509
TALIESIN: I'm going to try and cast Hold Person on
the creature.

02:12:00.509 --> 02:12:03.952
LAURA: Wait, I'll wave my arms so he walks toward
me.

02:12:03.952 --> 02:12:05.988
MATT: Make an intelligence check.

02:12:05.988 --> 02:12:08.210
TALIESIN: God, it won't work on him, will it?

02:12:08.210 --> 02:12:11.763
MATT: Yeah, so the creature heads over and it's
focused on you. What'd you get?

02:12:11.763 --> 02:12:13.787
TALIESIN: I got 20.

02:12:13.787 --> 02:12:18.876
MATT: 20. You get the sense that Hold Person
mainly affects small humanoid creatures. A large

02:12:18.876 --> 02:12:20.813
elemental like this would not be held by a spell.

02:12:20.813 --> 02:12:22.581
LAURA: Is an elemental considered a monster?

02:12:22.581 --> 02:12:24.169
MATT: It's considered a monster.

02:12:24.169 --> 02:12:25.445
TRAVIS: Creature, though.

02:12:25.445 --> 02:12:29.088
MATT: So you discovered your weapon.

02:12:29.088 --> 02:12:35.998
LIAM: Yes. This was made for me. Should I be
describing this to the table? Yes, this is called

02:12:35.998 --> 02:12:42.284
Adventurefury, Blessed Blade of the Thrillseeker.
This weirdly pristine longsword is encased in

02:12:42.284 --> 02:12:47.172
meticulous, almost gaudy, gold scrolling and
rune-like carvings that spell out phrases like,

02:12:47.172 --> 02:12:53.831
"Carpe Diem", like your shirt with donut, and "You
only live once." You gain plus two to all attacks

02:12:53.831 --> 02:12:58.267
and damage rolls made with this weapon. You are
immune to fear and, if you ever attempt to flee

02:12:58.267 --> 02:13:04.859
from danger, you must make a wisdom saving throw,
DC 12. On a failure, you instead rush toward the

02:13:04.859 --> 02:13:07.435
challenge in hopes of glory. YOLO!

02:13:07.435 --> 02:13:10.067
TRAVIS: Yes! That's a great item!

02:13:10.067 --> 02:13:12.272
MATT: It's Adventurefury, Blessed Blade of the
Thrillseeker.

02:13:12.272 --> 02:13:14.871
TRAVIS: Oh my god! Damn!

02:13:14.871 --> 02:13:16.601
LAURA: Is that an actual blade in the game?

02:13:16.601 --> 02:13:17.781
MATT: (chuckling) No.

02:13:17.781 --> 02:13:20.309
LAURA: Please make it an actual weapon in the
game.

02:13:20.309 --> 02:13:23.079
MATT: It's an inside joke.

02:13:23.079 --> 02:13:27.238
LIAM: For Argus and for LRJenkins1234.

02:13:27.238 --> 02:13:35.404
TRAVIS: I could try to stun him if we all wanted
to make a break for one side or the other. I'm not

02:13:35.404 --> 02:13:39.257
sure if it would work, so, any other ideas?

02:13:39.257 --> 02:13:41.862
JENNIFER: Which side?

02:13:41.862 --> 02:13:47.093
LAURA: Straight through, I think! I mean, that's
what Reek said.

02:13:47.093 --> 02:13:48.593
TRAVIS: Wasn't Reek lying?

02:13:48.593 --> 02:13:51.085
LAURA: No! He's very trustworthy.

02:13:51.085 --> 02:13:55.247
JENNIFER: I think there's something on the other
side that we don't know. We need to know.

02:13:55.247 --> 02:13:57.438
TRAVIS: I cast Zone of Truth.

02:13:57.438 --> 02:14:04.687
MATT: Okay. What's your spell DC? Oh, 13, right?
Nope.

02:14:04.687 --> 02:14:05.996
LAURA: Yay!

02:14:05.996 --> 02:14:13.565
TRAVIS: Cheeker-- what's his name? Oh, right,
Reek.

02:14:13.565 --> 02:14:16.081
MATT: "Reeksus."

02:14:16.081 --> 02:14:21.007
TRAVIS: Do you really know the way back to
Tagwaggle?

02:14:21.007 --> 02:14:22.823
MATT: "I do, yes!"

02:14:22.823 --> 02:14:24.478
TRAVIS: Which direction is it?

02:14:24.478 --> 02:14:29.072
MATT: "That would be (straining) right!"

02:14:29.072 --> 02:14:34.660
LAURA: He lied to me!

02:14:34.660 --> 02:14:38.175
TRAVIS: He did. I'm sure it's nothing personal,
though!

02:14:38.175 --> 02:14:39.954
MATT: "I'm bad with directions!"

02:14:39.954 --> 02:14:49.900
LAURA: He's telling the truth! Do you like us?
Aww. Do you like me?

02:14:49.900 --> 02:14:52.495
TRAVIS: No, he has to answer.

02:14:52.495 --> 02:14:56.157
MATT: "I endure you!"

02:14:56.157 --> 02:14:58.637
LAURA: I'll take it!

02:14:58.637 --> 02:15:00.783
MATT: I endure you.

02:15:00.783 --> 02:15:03.596
LIAM: Hey, Shakira, do you fear me?

02:15:03.596 --> 02:15:05.624
MATT: (panicked wimper)

02:15:05.624 --> 02:15:08.082
LIAM: Good, that's all that matters. Let's go.

02:15:08.082 --> 02:15:09.489
LAURA: I think I'm running out of my ten minutes.

02:15:09.489 --> 02:15:11.277
MATT: You're getting down to the last couple of
minutes.

02:15:11.277 --> 02:15:14.137
LAURA: I need to stand up and I need to fly away
from this place, or else I'm going to be stranded

02:15:14.137 --> 02:15:15.316
on this side!

02:15:15.316 --> 02:15:16.919
TALIESIN: You can land wherever we need to be.

02:15:16.919 --> 02:15:19.867
LAURA: Yeah, that's what I'm going to do, but I want to
fly around to the other side.

02:15:19.867 --> 02:15:24.710
MATT: Okay, so you coast around to this platform
over here and land on the opposite side of the

02:15:24.710 --> 02:15:28.759
bridge. The magma rager spins and is flexing in
the direction of where you are.

02:15:28.759 --> 02:15:32.704
TRAVIS: While the Zone of Truth is still active,
Bundle, what are you the most afraid of?

02:15:32.704 --> 02:15:36.451
MATT: Make a wisdom saving throw.

02:15:36.451 --> 02:15:48.324
TALIESIN: Oh! That's a 24.

02:15:48.324 --> 02:15:49.844
MATT: Answer as you feel.

02:15:49.844 --> 02:15:58.076
TALIESIN: Not you. Not even a little. You're so
soft and squishy.

02:15:58.076 --> 02:16:01.530
TRAVIS: No, see, if it was a spider, then I could
take care of it for you. I don't want to leave you

02:16:01.530 --> 02:16:03.133
in an awkward situation.

02:16:03.133 --> 02:16:04.646
JENNIFER: Should we leave you two alone?

02:16:04.646 --> 02:16:05.839
TALIESIN: No.

02:16:05.839 --> 02:16:07.534
MATT: "Yes!"

02:16:07.534 --> 02:16:11.848
TALIESIN: Well, you only live once.

02:16:11.848 --> 02:16:14.118
LAURA: What are you going to do?

02:16:14.118 --> 02:16:16.216
TRAVIS: Do it.

02:16:16.216 --> 02:16:18.323
TALIESIN: I'm going to make a run for it. Fuck
it.

02:16:18.323 --> 02:16:19.704
MATT: What's your strength?

02:16:19.704 --> 02:16:24.024
TALIESIN: My strength is 16.

02:16:24.024 --> 02:16:31.665
MATT: 16? That's easy enough for you. You run and
leap, big dwarven strong legs. You leap across. You

02:16:31.665 --> 02:16:38.969
land on the center platform, at which point the
magma rager turns to face you. What are you

02:16:38.969 --> 02:16:40.606
doing?

02:16:40.606 --> 02:16:44.919
TALIESIN: I'm going to cast Sacred Flame, which I
know will do very little on him, but it might

02:16:44.919 --> 02:16:50.049
temporarily irritate him. I'm going to run the
opposite direction.

02:16:50.049 --> 02:16:54.992
MATT: Okay, Sacred Flame. So he makes a dexterity
saving throw. No, it's an action to do that.

02:16:54.992 --> 02:16:58.137
TALIESIN: Oh, it's an action to do that? Should I
burn my action running?

02:16:58.137 --> 02:17:04.216
MATT: To dash? You can, if you want to. Okay, you
go running as it goes charging toward you. It's

02:17:04.216 --> 02:17:14.751
going to go ahead and attempt to make a
charge-slam attack. That is going to be a 23 to

02:17:14.751 --> 02:17:16.433
hit.

02:17:16.433 --> 02:17:18.266
TALIESIN: Oh my god, yeah, that hits.

02:17:18.266 --> 02:17:21.090
MATT: Double ones on the attack, so only six
points of bludgeoning damage.

02:17:21.090 --> 02:17:22.391
TALIESIN: I can live with that.

02:17:22.391 --> 02:17:23.822
MATT: Six points of fire damage.

02:17:23.822 --> 02:17:25.240
TALIESIN: I can live with that too.

02:17:25.240 --> 02:17:30.734
MATT: As it slams into you, you immediately get
pushed 15 feet back into the air. You arc

02:17:30.734 --> 02:17:36.532
backwards. As you're falling back, you can look,
you're edging toward where the central platform

02:17:36.532 --> 02:17:40.356
where you were before you go to the middle one,
and off to the side where the lava is. Go ahead

02:17:40.356 --> 02:17:41.985
and make an acrobatics check.

02:17:41.985 --> 02:17:48.143
TALIESIN: God, if I have to do an action, I hope I
can get an action before this happens. Acrobatics

02:17:48.143 --> 02:17:49.438
check, oh god.

02:17:49.438 --> 02:17:51.181
TRAVIS: Why'd you give the Snitch back?!

02:17:51.181 --> 02:17:52.876
TALIESIN: Because I'm an idiot! 20.

02:17:52.876 --> 02:17:58.757
MATT: 20? You barely manage to catch yourself on
the edge and roll back up (straining) onto the

02:17:58.757 --> 02:18:05.076
platform. The magma rager is right there staring
at you, its burning coal magma eyes angrily

02:18:05.076 --> 02:18:06.865
staring at your dwarven form.

02:18:06.865 --> 02:18:08.653
TALIESIN: So where am I now?

02:18:08.653 --> 02:18:11.729
MATT: You are now currently right here in the
center, yeah.

02:18:11.729 --> 02:18:13.649
LAURA: Oh, he ran backwards?

02:18:13.649 --> 02:18:16.982
MATT: He slammed into him as he ran toward him and
pushed him back onto the middle platform. At least

02:18:16.982 --> 02:18:18.684
he didn't fall in.

02:18:18.684 --> 02:18:25.209
LAURA: Okay, I have an idea. Is he considered
fighting us right now, or is he just staring?

02:18:25.209 --> 02:18:30.800
MATT: I mean, in theory, it can't seemingly do
anything at you from range, so he's waiting for

02:18:30.800 --> 02:18:35.502
somebody to come to his platform. If you decide to
then assault him on the middle platform, there'd

02:18:35.502 --> 02:18:38.327
be an initiative roll. But right now it doesn't
seem to have any means of attacking at range.

02:18:38.327 --> 02:18:42.997
LAURA: Okay, then I'm going to cast Charm Monster
on the creature.

02:18:42.997 --> 02:18:45.223
MATT: Okay. So this is your 4th-level?

02:18:45.223 --> 02:18:46.501
LAURA: It is.

02:18:46.501 --> 02:18:48.572
MATT: It rolled a four, so it does not succeed.

02:18:48.572 --> 02:18:54.862
LAURA: Woo! You love us! We're really great! Let
us pass!

02:18:54.862 --> 02:19:03.274
MATT: You watch as its intense expression toward
the dwarf slackens and it flexes its shoulders and

02:19:03.274 --> 02:19:08.214
then roils back to the center platform and then
looks over toward you with a nod.

02:19:08.214 --> 02:19:15.729
LAURA: Your mama loves you very much. Your papa's
very proud of you. Come on, you guys.

02:19:15.729 --> 02:19:17.998
TRAVIS: Doesn't seem so scary! Across.

02:19:17.998 --> 02:19:20.947
MATT: All right, so your strength, your strength.
What's your strength?

02:19:20.947 --> 02:19:24.069
JENNIFER: Ah, zero. Or ten, sorry, ten.

02:19:24.069 --> 02:19:26.691
LAURA: Nobody attack him, guys. If anybody touches
him, this is going to break.

02:19:26.691 --> 02:19:31.157
MATT: Yeah, so the three of you make it across
fine without any issue. Go ahead and make an

02:19:31.157 --> 02:19:32.996
acrobatics check for me.

02:19:32.996 --> 02:19:35.108
LIAM: 20. Natural 20.

02:19:35.108 --> 02:19:39.941
MATT: I'll let that go for all of them. With a
natural 20, seeing this happen and watching them

02:19:39.941 --> 02:19:45.754
all dart across, you begin to do hand-over-feet,
full-on handspring-style leaping over the

02:19:45.754 --> 02:19:50.624
platforms past the rager. You all make it over to
the side platform, meeting up with your mage

02:19:50.624 --> 02:19:54.055
friend as the magma rager's still sitting there,
resting in the center, looking toward you for some

02:19:54.055 --> 02:19:55.625
sort of an order.

02:19:55.625 --> 02:19:56.744
TRAVIS: I did have Reeksus with me.

02:19:56.744 --> 02:20:05.231
MATT: (screeching) (impact) He's being dragged and
slammed like some horrible, slow-motion yo-yo.

02:20:05.231 --> 02:20:08.608
TALIESIN: I did a quick Cure Wounds back to 41.

02:20:08.608 --> 02:20:10.974
LAURA: Can you talk, magma monster?

02:20:10.974 --> 02:20:19.395
MATT: You hear it emitting some sort of sound, but
it sounds like a heavy bonfire and rocks banging

02:20:19.395 --> 02:20:20.835
together.

02:20:20.835 --> 02:20:28.078
LAURA: You know what friends do? They dance.
Friends dance with each other. We should dance.

02:20:28.078 --> 02:20:33.176
MATT: So as you step up to the edge of the
platform, begin to gnome-dance, the rager--

02:20:33.176 --> 02:20:37.180
LIAM: Is it the Warcraft dancing animation?

02:20:37.180 --> 02:20:38.863
