03:55:06.911 --> 03:55:09.899
brighten once more. What are you guys doing?

03:55:09.899 --> 03:55:11.268
LAURA: Jumping into the latrine!

03:55:11.268 --> 03:55:15.231
TRAVIS: Yeah, jump into the latrine, and maybe let
the raging current take us wherever.

03:55:15.231 --> 03:55:16.529
JENNIFER: It goes somewhere.

03:55:16.529 --> 03:55:21.838
MATT: The rushing river, you mean? Okay.

03:55:21.838 --> 03:55:29.304
LIAM: Right, so we make a run, and I make a wisdom
save, and I fail, so I turn around and go back. I

03:55:29.304 --> 03:55:30.500
drop my candles.

03:55:30.500 --> 03:55:34.598
MATT: All of you guys dive into the water, letting
the water take you like a water slide, one after

03:55:34.598 --> 03:55:43.538
the other, and you watch as Quazirat turns around
with Adventurefury, the Blessed Blade of the

03:55:43.538 --> 03:55:51.821
Thrill-Seeker in his hand, and knows, "No, this is
your fate. This is your glory." And the last thing

03:55:51.821 --> 03:55:55.915
you see before you all vanish into the water is
him scream and run towards the reformed

03:55:55.915 --> 03:55:58.255
Rakanishu's elemental form.

03:55:58.255 --> 03:56:02.524
LIAM: LRJenkins1234!

03:56:02.524 --> 03:56:05.294
JENNIFER: Your father's proud of you!

03:56:05.294 --> 03:56:12.070
MATT: So at this point, darkness takes over.
You're being rushed around the current. It's

03:56:12.070 --> 03:56:15.472
battering you around at a rapid speed. Even those
of you with darkvision, things are coming by so

03:56:15.472 --> 03:56:23.025
fast that you're only seeing things quick enough
before it impacts you. I need all of you to make a

03:56:23.025 --> 03:56:25.364
perception check. If you have darkvision, you make
it with advantage.

03:56:25.364 --> 03:56:32.426
TALIESIN: 19.

03:56:32.426 --> 03:56:33.911
MATT: Success.

03:56:33.911 --> 03:56:35.177
LAURA: 23.

03:56:35.177 --> 03:56:36.301
TRAVIS: 16.

03:56:36.301 --> 03:56:38.025
JENNIFER: 17.

03:56:38.025 --> 03:56:43.150
MATT: 17? Okay, you all succeed, so you only
suffer three points of bludgeoning damage as you

03:56:43.150 --> 03:56:45.911
guys are being battered around-- oh, you go limp
and unconscious.

03:56:45.911 --> 03:56:47.608
TRAVIS: Oh, you do?!

03:56:47.608 --> 03:56:49.302
JENNIFER: I only had two left.

03:56:49.302 --> 03:56:53.705
MATT: All right, as you're being thrust around
inside, the river's carrying you, and you're

03:56:53.705 --> 03:56:58.762
trying to hold your breath. The air escapes your
lungs. You guys all try your best to hold

03:56:58.762 --> 03:57:04.112
together. You hit another sequence of rock. Using
your perception from before, you still only suffer

03:57:04.112 --> 03:57:12.393
another seven points of bludgeoning amongst you,
so seven, seven-- actually, it would be half, so

03:57:12.393 --> 03:57:21.116
three to each of you. Eventually, after a minute
or so, your lungs begin to burn from holding in

03:57:21.116 --> 03:57:23.304
the air. What's your constitution?

03:57:23.304 --> 03:57:25.558
TRAVIS: 16.

03:57:25.558 --> 03:57:26.568
MATT: What about you?

03:57:26.568 --> 03:57:28.695
LAURA: 13.

03:57:28.695 --> 03:57:29.837
TALIESIN: 14.

03:57:29.837 --> 03:57:34.945
MATT: Okay, so your air begins to escape your
lungs. You can't hold it anymore and you begin to

03:57:34.945 --> 03:57:39.638
drown just as a light comes to you. All of a
sudden, the thrusting of water stops, and you're

03:57:39.638 --> 03:57:46.491
all free-floating in water, and you all begin to
scavenge around for any sense of what's up, what's

03:57:46.491 --> 03:57:51.797
down. The light is below you, the glow, and you
begin to right yourself and realize that that is

03:57:51.797 --> 03:57:56.578
actually above. You look up, and it looks to be
there's a surface of water. You all begin to swim

03:57:56.578 --> 03:58:01.298
up-- at least, those of you that are conscious.
You're struggling and drowning, and you limply

03:58:01.298 --> 03:58:03.529
begin to float to the surface.

03:58:03.529 --> 03:58:06.721
TALIESIN: Is she floating to the surface? I'm
going to follow her up, then.

03:58:06.721 --> 03:58:12.796
MATT: Okay. Make a constitution saving throw.

03:58:12.796 --> 03:58:15.500
TRAVIS: Is my plate mail a problem?

03:58:15.500 --> 03:58:18.966
MATT: You have a high constitution, so you're able
to hold your breath longer.

03:58:18.966 --> 03:58:22.210
(laughter)

03:58:22.210 --> 03:58:24.491
LAURA: Ten?

03:58:24.491 --> 03:58:29.772
MATT: Ten? You go unconscious and begin drowning.

03:58:29.772 --> 03:58:31.872
LAURA: Does that mean I start floating?

03:58:31.872 --> 03:58:36.075
MATT: You're scrambling under the water and go
limp and begin to slowly rise up, as well. Two of

03:58:36.075 --> 03:58:37.923
them begin to rise up in the water.

03:58:37.923 --> 03:58:39.301
LIAM: Rise up.

03:58:39.301 --> 03:58:46.845
MATT: All right, as you guys break the surface,
(gasping) you glance around, gasping in the cold

03:58:46.845 --> 03:58:52.596
air. The blue sky above you is nearly cloudless: a
welcome sight as you recognize the nearby docks

03:58:52.596 --> 03:58:58.371
and humble buildings of Lakeshore, where you once
left. You apparently were jettisoned to the bottom

03:58:58.371 --> 03:59:01.887
of Lake Everstill, and you're just around the
corner from where you started this venture.

03:59:01.887 --> 03:59:07.369
TALIESIN: Healing Word, level two; Healing Word,
level three.

03:59:07.369 --> 03:59:14.142
MATT: Okay, you come to consciousness. She's a
little worse for wear.

03:59:14.142 --> 03:59:18.131
LAURA: Oh no. Do you have Revivify?

03:59:18.131 --> 03:59:23.728
TALIESIN: If I use my Healing Word not knowing
that she was dead-- did I use my Healing Word not

03:59:23.728 --> 03:59:30.584
knowing she was dead? Because I'm out of magic, at
that point, if I've used two Healing Words.

03:59:30.584 --> 03:59:32.884
MATT: Make a medicine check.

03:59:32.884 --> 03:59:34.455
TALIESIN: All right, that'll do.

03:59:34.455 --> 03:59:36.798
LIAM: Also, did his spell reach three miles back?

03:59:36.798 --> 03:59:38.154
MATT: No.

03:59:38.154 --> 03:59:40.192
TALIESIN: Oh! 24.

03:59:40.192 --> 03:59:45.010
MATT: 24? Glancing over as you begin to cast the
spell, you recognize the signs that she is not--

03:59:45.010 --> 03:59:48.455
TALIESIN: Revivify on this one, Healing Word at
level two on this one.

03:59:48.455 --> 03:59:53.283
MATT: Okay, I'll allow that. For the purposes of
this, you reach over, and from the cold shackles

03:59:53.283 --> 04:00:02.431
of death, the spirit of Aerwin, who went on to
greet the goddess Elune, is pulled back into her

04:00:02.431 --> 04:00:05.768
form as she gasps for breath back at the surface
and begins to paddle.

04:00:05.768 --> 04:00:08.523
TALIESIN: Big dwarven punch in the face. Wake up!

04:00:08.523 --> 04:00:15.199
MATT: The four of you slowly scramble and make
your way towards the shores of Lake Everstill.

04:00:15.199 --> 04:00:27.219
Waterlogged and down one ally, you make your way,
beaten and bruised. So you have two satchels of

04:00:27.219 --> 04:00:34.952
no-longer-soft candles, and you make your way
inside Lakeshore Inn, which has another patron

04:00:34.952 --> 04:00:39.844
now, so business is booming. You see as Wental
turns around as you enter and goes, "My goodness,

04:00:39.844 --> 04:00:47.910
"friends! You've returned! Oh, and a little worse
for wear, but where's your friend with the

04:00:47.910 --> 04:00:49.025
"beard?"

04:00:49.025 --> 04:00:50.116
TRAVIS: He died.

04:00:50.116 --> 04:00:52.030
LAURA: He died getting your candles.

04:00:52.030 --> 04:00:53.539
TALIESIN: You owe us lunch.

04:00:53.539 --> 04:00:59.524
MATT: "I'm terribly sorry, but food can be
prepared. That's a shame. But did you get my

04:00:59.524 --> 04:01:00.867
"candles?"

04:01:00.867 --> 04:01:02.065
TRAVIS: Show him the bag.

04:01:02.065 --> 04:01:11.058
MATT: As you dump out a solid rock of wax onto the
wooden table, he glances down.

04:01:11.058 --> 04:01:19.945
LAURA: Those creatures, they had melted all of
your candles already. We saved as much wax as we

04:01:19.945 --> 04:01:21.501
could for you.

04:01:21.501 --> 04:01:30.400
MATT: "Let me go make some breakfast." As he
shell-shockedly makes his way towards the kitchen,

04:01:30.400 --> 04:01:37.082
you all sit down, pull the wooden chairs out, slap
down on the table, water still dripping from your

04:01:37.082 --> 04:01:45.107
armor and clothes. You sit there, grab whatever
half-drunk tankards you left as you exited, finish

04:01:45.107 --> 04:01:53.577
them off, make eye contact, and think, "Man, can
it really be worse up on Argus right about now?"

04:01:53.577 --> 04:01:56.349
And that's where we'll close today's game.

04:01:56.349 --> 04:01:59.710
(cheering)

04:01:59.710 --> 04:02:01.829
LAURA: Oh no, poor Toes!

04:02:01.829 --> 04:02:04.231
LIAM: Will one of you please look after my WoW
account?

04:02:04.231 --> 04:02:09.364
JENNIFER: Absolutely.

04:02:09.364 --> 04:02:11.620
MATT: Thank you guys so much for playing. Thank
you, Jen, for coming and joining us.

04:02:11.620 --> 04:02:16.304
JENNIFER: Thank you! This was so fun. Thank you.
Amazing.

04:02:16.304 --> 04:02:20.319
MATT: Thank you guys for coming and joining us.
Thank you very much to Blizzard for working with

04:02:20.319 --> 04:02:26.699
us and putting this together and letting us play
